It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

42// Macro for outputting trace information from representation inference.
43#define TRACE(...) \
44 do { \
45 if (v8_flags.trace_representation) PrintF(__VA_ARGS__); \
46 } while (false)

48const char* kSimplifiedLoweringReducerName = "SimplifiedLowering";
49
50// Representation selection and lowering of {Simplified} operators to machine
51// operators are interwined. We use a fixpoint calculation to compute both the
52// output representation and the best possible lowering for {Simplified} nodes.
53// Representation change insertion ensures that all values are in the correct
54// machine representation after this phase, as dictated by the machine
55// operators themselves.
56enum Phase {
57 // 1.) PROPAGATE: Traverse the graph from the end, pushing usage information
58 // backwards from uses to definitions, around cycles in phis, according
59 // to local rules for each operator.
60 // During this phase, the usage information for a node determines the best
61 // possible lowering for each operator so far, and that in turn determines
62 // the output representation.
63 // Therefore, to be correct, this phase must iterate to a fixpoint before
64 // the next phase can begin.
65 PROPAGATE,
66
67 // 2.) RETYPE: Propagate types from type feedback forwards.
68 RETYPE,
69
70 // 3.) LOWER: perform lowering for all {Simplified} nodes by replacing some
71 // operators for some nodes, expanding some nodes to multiple nodes, or
72 // removing some (redundant) nodes.
73 // During this phase, use the {RepresentationChanger} to insert
74 // representation changes between uses that demand a particular
75 // representation and nodes that produce a different representation.
76 LOWER
77};
78
79namespace {

81MachineRepresentation MachineRepresentationFromArrayType(
82 ExternalArrayType array_type) {
83 switch (array_type) {
84 case kExternalUint8Array:
85 case kExternalUint8ClampedArray:
86 case kExternalInt8Array:
87 return MachineRepresentation::kWord8;
88 case kExternalUint16Array:
89 case kExternalInt16Array:
90 return MachineRepresentation::kWord16;
91 case kExternalUint32Array:
92 case kExternalInt32Array:
93 return MachineRepresentation::kWord32;
94 case kExternalFloat32Array:
95 return MachineRepresentation::kFloat32;
96 case kExternalFloat64Array:
97 return MachineRepresentation::kFloat64;
98 case kExternalBigInt64Array:
99 case kExternalBigUint64Array:
100 return MachineRepresentation::kWord64;
101 case kExternalFloat16Array:
102 UNIMPLEMENTED();
103 }
104 UNREACHABLE();
105}
106
107UseInfo CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(
108 NumberOperationHint hint, IdentifyZeros identify_zeros = kDistinguishZeros,
109 const FeedbackSource& feedback = FeedbackSource()) {
110 switch (hint) {
111 case NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall:
112 case NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs:
113 return UseInfo::CheckedSignedSmallAsWord32(identify_zeros, feedback);
114 case NumberOperationHint::kNumber:
115 DCHECK_EQ(identify_zeros, kIdentifyZeros);
116 return UseInfo::CheckedNumberAsWord32(feedback);
117 case NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrBoolean:
118 // Not used currently.
119 UNREACHABLE();
120 case NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball:
121 DCHECK_EQ(identify_zeros, kIdentifyZeros);
122 return UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsWord32(feedback);
123 }
124 UNREACHABLE();
125}
126
127UseInfo CheckedUseInfoAsFloat64FromHint(
128 NumberOperationHint hint, const FeedbackSource& feedback,
129 IdentifyZeros identify_zeros = kDistinguishZeros) {
130 switch (hint) {
131 case NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall:
132 case NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs:
133 // Not used currently.
134 UNREACHABLE();
135 case NumberOperationHint::kNumber:
136 return UseInfo::CheckedNumberAsFloat64(identify_zeros, feedback);
137 case NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrBoolean:
138 return UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrBooleanAsFloat64(identify_zeros, feedback);
139 case NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball:
140 return UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64(identify_zeros, feedback);
141 }
142 UNREACHABLE();
143}
144
145UseInfo TruncatingUseInfoFromRepresentation(MachineRepresentation rep) {
146 switch (rep) {
147 case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned:
148 return UseInfo::TaggedSigned();
149 case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer:
150 case MachineRepresentation::kTagged:
151 case MachineRepresentation::kIndirectPointer:
152 case MachineRepresentation::kMapWord:
153 return UseInfo::AnyTagged();
154 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64:
155 return UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64();
156 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16:
157 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
158 return UseInfo::Float32();
159 case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
160 case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
161 case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
162 return UseInfo::TruncatingWord32();
163 case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
164 return UseInfo::TruncatingWord64();
165 case MachineRepresentation::kBit:
166 return UseInfo::Bool();
167 case MachineRepresentation::kCompressedPointer:
168 case MachineRepresentation::kCompressed:
169 case MachineRepresentation::kProtectedPointer:
170 case MachineRepresentation::kSandboxedPointer:
171 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
172 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd256:
173 case MachineRepresentation::kNone:
174 UNREACHABLE();
175 }
176}

178UseInfo UseInfoForBasePointer(const FieldAccess& access) {
179 return access.tag() != 0 ? UseInfo::AnyTagged() : UseInfo::Word();
180}
181
182UseInfo UseInfoForBasePointer(const ElementAccess& access) {
183 return access.tag() != 0 ? UseInfo::AnyTagged() : UseInfo::Word();

186void ReplaceEffectControlUses(Node* node, Node* effect, Node* control) {
187 for (Edge edge : node->use_edges()) {
188 if (NodeProperties::IsControlEdge(edge)) {
189 edge.UpdateTo(control);
190 } else if (NodeProperties::IsEffectEdge(edge)) {
191 edge.UpdateTo(effect);
192 } else {
193 DCHECK(NodeProperties::IsValueEdge(edge) ||
194 NodeProperties::IsContextEdge(edge));
195 }
196 }
197}
198
199bool CanOverflowSigned32(const Operator* op, Type left, Type right,
200 TypeCache const* type_cache, Zone* type_zone) {
201 // We assume the inputs are checked Signed32 (or known statically to be
202 // Signed32). Technically, the inputs could also be minus zero, which we treat
203 // as 0 for the purpose of this function.
204 if (left.Maybe(Type::MinusZero())) {
205 left = Type::Union(left, type_cache->kSingletonZero, type_zone);
206 }
207 if (right.Maybe(Type::MinusZero())) {
208 right = Type::Union(right, type_cache->kSingletonZero, type_zone);
209 }
210 left = Type::Intersect(left, Type::Signed32(), type_zone);
211 right = Type::Intersect(right, Type::Signed32(), type_zone);
212 if (left.IsNone() || right.IsNone()) return false;
213 switch (op->opcode()) {
214 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeSafeIntegerAdd:
215 return (left.Max() + right.Max() > kMaxInt) ||
216 (left.Min() + right.Min() < kMinInt);
217
218 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeSafeIntegerSubtract:
219 return (left.Max() - right.Min() > kMaxInt) ||
220 (left.Min() - right.Max() < kMinInt);
221
222 default:
223 UNREACHABLE();
224 }
225}
226
227bool IsSomePositiveOrderedNumber(Type type) {
228 return type.Is(Type::OrderedNumber()) && (type.IsNone() || type.Min() > 0);
229}
230
231inline bool IsLargeBigInt(Type type) {
232 return type.Is(Type::BigInt()) && !type.Is(Type::SignedBigInt64()) &&
233 !type.Is(Type::UnsignedBigInt64());
234}

255#ifdef DEBUG
256// Helpers for monotonicity checking.
257class InputUseInfos {
258 public:
259 explicit InputUseInfos(Zone* zone) : input_use_infos_(zone) {}
260
261 void SetAndCheckInput(Node* node, int index, UseInfo use_info) {
262 if (input_use_infos_.empty()) {
263 input_use_infos_.resize(node->InputCount(), UseInfo::None());
264 }
265 // Check that the new use informatin is a super-type of the old
266 // one.
267 DCHECK(IsUseLessGeneral(input_use_infos_[index], use_info));
268 input_use_infos_[index] = use_info;
269 }
270
271 private:
272 ZoneVector<UseInfo> input_use_infos_;
273
274 static bool IsUseLessGeneral(UseInfo use1, UseInfo use2) {
275 return use1.truncation().IsLessGeneralThan(use2.truncation());
276 }
277};

281class RepresentationSelector {
282 // The purpose of this nested class is to hide method
283 // v8::internal::compiler::NodeProperties::ChangeOp which should not be
284 // directly used by code in RepresentationSelector and SimplifiedLowering.
285 // RepresentationSelector code should call RepresentationSelector::ChangeOp in
286 // place of NodeProperties::ChangeOp, in order to notify the changes to a
287 // registered ObserveNodeManager and support the %ObserveNode intrinsic.
288 class NodeProperties : public compiler::NodeProperties {
289 static void ChangeOp(Node* node, const Operator* new_op) { UNREACHABLE(); }
290 };
291
292 public:
293 // Information for each node tracked during the fixpoint.
294 class NodeInfo final {
295 public:
296 // Adds new use to the node. Returns true if something has changed
297 // and the node has to be requeued.
298 bool AddUse(UseInfo info) {
299 Truncation old_truncation = truncation_;
300 truncation_ = Truncation::Generalize(truncation_, info.truncation());
301 return truncation_ != old_truncation;
302 }
303
304 void set_queued() { state_ = kQueued; }
305 void set_visited() { state_ = kVisited; }
306 void set_pushed() { state_ = kPushed; }
307 void reset_state() { state_ = kUnvisited; }
308 bool visited() const { return state_ == kVisited; }
309 bool queued() const { return state_ == kQueued; }
310 bool pushed() const { return state_ == kPushed; }
311 bool unvisited() const { return state_ == kUnvisited; }
312 Truncation truncation() const { return truncation_; }
313 void set_output(MachineRepresentation output) { representation_ = output; }
314
315 MachineRepresentation representation() const { return representation_; }
316
317 // Helpers for feedback typing.
318 void set_feedback_type(Type type) { feedback_type_ = type; }
319 Type feedback_type() const { return feedback_type_; }
320 void set_weakened() { weakened_ = true; }
321 bool weakened() const { return weakened_; }
322 void set_restriction_type(Type type) { restriction_type_ = type; }
323 Type restriction_type() const { return restriction_type_; }
324
325 private:
326 // Fields are ordered to avoid mixing byte and word size fields to minimize
327 // padding.
328 enum State : uint8_t { kUnvisited, kPushed, kVisited, kQueued };
329 State state_ = kUnvisited;
330 MachineRepresentation representation_ =
331 MachineRepresentation::kNone; // Output representation.
332 Truncation truncation_ = Truncation::None(); // Information about uses.
333 bool weakened_ = false;
334
335 Type restriction_type_ = Type::Any();
336 Type feedback_type_;
337 };

339 RepresentationSelector(JSGraph* jsgraph, JSHeapBroker* broker, Zone* zone,
340 RepresentationChanger* changer,
341 SourcePositionTable* source_positions,
342 NodeOriginTable* node_origins,
343 TickCounter* tick_counter, Linkage* linkage,
344 ObserveNodeManager* observe_node_manager,
345 SimplifiedLoweringVerifier* verifier)
346 : jsgraph_(jsgraph),
347 broker_(broker),
348 zone_(zone),
349 might_need_revisit_(zone),
350 count_(jsgraph->graph()->NodeCount()),
351 info_(count_, zone),
352#ifdef DEBUG
353 node_input_use_infos_(count_, InputUseInfos(zone), zone),
354#endif
355 replacements_(zone),
356 changer_(changer),
357 revisit_queue_(zone),
358 traversal_nodes_(zone),
359 source_positions_(source_positions),
360 node_origins_(node_origins),
361 type_cache_(TypeCache::Get()),
362 op_typer_(broker, graph_zone()),
363 tick_counter_(tick_counter),
364 linkage_(linkage),
365 observe_node_manager_(observe_node_manager),
366 verifier_(verifier) {
367 singleton_true_ =
368 Type::Constant(broker, broker->true_value(), graph_zone());
369 singleton_false_ =
370 Type::Constant(broker, broker->false_value(), graph_zone());
371 }

373 bool verification_enabled() const { return verifier_ != nullptr; }
374
375 void ResetNodeInfoState() {
376 // Clean up for the next phase.
377 for (NodeInfo& info : info_) {
378 info.reset_state();
379 }
380 }
381
382 Type TypeOf(Node* node) {
383 Type type = GetInfo(node)->feedback_type();
384 return type.IsInvalid() ? NodeProperties::GetType(node) : type;
385 }
386
387 Type FeedbackTypeOf(Node* node) {
388 Type type = GetInfo(node)->feedback_type();
389 return type.IsInvalid() ? Type::None() : type;
390 }
391
392 Type TypePhi(Node* node) {
393 int arity = node->op()->ValueInputCount();
394 Type type = FeedbackTypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
395 for (int i = 1; i < arity; ++i) {
396 type = op_typer_.Merge(type, FeedbackTypeOf(node->InputAt(i)));
397 }
398 return type;
399 }
400
401 Type TypeSelect(Node* node) {
402 return op_typer_.Merge(FeedbackTypeOf(node->InputAt(1)),
403 FeedbackTypeOf(node->InputAt(2)));
404 }
405
406 bool UpdateFeedbackType(Node* node) {
407 if (node->op()->ValueOutputCount() == 0) return false;
408 if ((IrOpcode::IsMachineOpcode(node->opcode()) ||
409 IrOpcode::IsMachineConstantOpcode(node->opcode())) &&
410 node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kLoadFramePointer) {
411 DCHECK(NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Machine()));
412 }
413
414 // For any non-phi node just wait until we get all inputs typed. We only
415 // allow untyped inputs for phi nodes because phis are the only places
416 // where cycles need to be broken.
417 if (node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kPhi) {
418 for (int i = 0; i < node->op()->ValueInputCount(); i++) {
419 if (GetInfo(node->InputAt(i))->feedback_type().IsInvalid()) {
420 return false;
421 }
422 }
423 }
424
425 NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node);
426 Type type = info->feedback_type();
427 Type new_type = NodeProperties::GetType(node);
428
429 // We preload these values here to avoid increasing the binary size too
430 // much, which happens if we inline the calls into the macros below.
431 Type input0_type;
432 if (node->InputCount() > 0) input0_type = FeedbackTypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
433 Type input1_type;
434 if (node->InputCount() > 1) input1_type = FeedbackTypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
435
436 switch (node->opcode()) {
437#define DECLARE_CASE(Name) \
438 case IrOpcode::k##Name: { \
439 new_type = op_typer_.Name(input0_type, input1_type); \
440 break; \
441 }
442 SIMPLIFIED_NUMBER_BINOP_LIST(DECLARE_CASE)
443 DECLARE_CASE(SameValue)
444#undef DECLARE_CASE
445
446#define DECLARE_CASE(Name) \
447 case IrOpcode::k##Name: { \
448 new_type = Type::Intersect(op_typer_.Name(input0_type, input1_type), \
449 info->restriction_type(), graph_zone()); \
450 break; \
451 }
452 SIMPLIFIED_SPECULATIVE_NUMBER_BINOP_LIST(DECLARE_CASE)
453 SIMPLIFIED_SPECULATIVE_BIGINT_BINOP_LIST(DECLARE_CASE)
454#undef DECLARE_CASE
455
456#define DECLARE_CASE(Name) \
457 case IrOpcode::k##Name: { \
458 new_type = op_typer_.Name(input0_type); \
459 break; \
460 }
461 SIMPLIFIED_NUMBER_UNOP_LIST(DECLARE_CASE)
462#undef DECLARE_CASE
463
464#define DECLARE_CASE(Name) \
465 case IrOpcode::k##Name: { \
466 new_type = Type::Intersect(op_typer_.Name(input0_type), \
467 info->restriction_type(), graph_zone()); \
468 break; \
469 }
470 SIMPLIFIED_SPECULATIVE_NUMBER_UNOP_LIST(DECLARE_CASE)
471#undef DECLARE_CASE
472
473 case IrOpcode::kConvertReceiver:
474 new_type = op_typer_.ConvertReceiver(input0_type);
475 break;
476
477 case IrOpcode::kPlainPrimitiveToNumber:
478 new_type = op_typer_.ToNumber(input0_type);
479 break;
480
481 case IrOpcode::kCheckBounds:
482 new_type =
483 Type::Intersect(op_typer_.CheckBounds(input0_type, input1_type),
484 info->restriction_type(), graph_zone());
485 break;
486
487 case IrOpcode::kCheckFloat64Hole:
488 new_type = Type::Intersect(op_typer_.CheckFloat64Hole(input0_type),
489 info->restriction_type(), graph_zone());
490 break;
491
492 case IrOpcode::kCheckNumber:
493 new_type = Type::Intersect(op_typer_.CheckNumber(input0_type),
494 info->restriction_type(), graph_zone());
495 break;
496
497 case IrOpcode::kCheckNumberFitsInt32:
498 new_type = Type::Intersect(op_typer_.CheckNumberFitsInt32(input0_type),
499 info->restriction_type(), graph_zone());
500 break;
501
502 case IrOpcode::kPhi: {
503 new_type = TypePhi(node);
504 if (!type.IsInvalid()) {
505 new_type = Weaken(node, type, new_type);
506 }
507 break;
508 }
509
510 case IrOpcode::kConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined:
511 new_type = op_typer_.ConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined(
512 FeedbackTypeOf(node->InputAt(0)));
513 break;
514
515 case IrOpcode::kTypeGuard: {
516 new_type = op_typer_.TypeTypeGuard(node->op(),
517 FeedbackTypeOf(node->InputAt(0)));
518 break;
519 }
520
521 case IrOpcode::kSelect: {
522 const auto& p = SelectParametersOf(node->op());
523 if (p.semantics() == BranchSemantics::kMachine) {
524 if (type.IsInvalid()) {
525 GetInfo(node)->set_feedback_type(NodeProperties::GetType(node));
526 return true;
527 }
528 return false;
529 }
530 new_type = TypeSelect(node);
531 break;
532 }
533
534 default:
535 // Shortcut for operations that we do not handle.
536 if (type.IsInvalid()) {
537 GetInfo(node)->set_feedback_type(NodeProperties::GetType(node));
538 return true;
539 }
540 return false;
541 }
542 // We need to guarantee that the feedback type is a subtype of the upper
543 // bound. Naively that should hold, but weakening can actually produce
544 // a bigger type if we are unlucky with ordering of phi typing. To be
545 // really sure, just intersect the upper bound with the feedback type.
546 new_type = Type::Intersect(GetUpperBound(node), new_type, graph_zone());
547
548 if (!type.IsInvalid() && new_type.Is(type)) return false;
549 GetInfo(node)->set_feedback_type(new_type);
550 if (v8_flags.trace_representation) {
551 PrintNodeFeedbackType(node);
552 }
553 return true;
554 }
555
556 void PrintNodeFeedbackType(Node* n) {
557 StdoutStream os;
558 os << "#" << n->id() << ":" << *n->op() << "(";
559 int j = 0;
560 for (Node* const i : n->inputs()) {
561 if (j++ > 0) os << ", ";
562 os << "#" << i->id() << ":" << i->op()->mnemonic();
563 }
564 os << ")";
565 if (NodeProperties::IsTyped(n)) {
566 Type static_type = NodeProperties::GetType(n);
567 os << " [Static type: " << static_type;
568 Type feedback_type = GetInfo(n)->feedback_type();
569 if (!feedback_type.IsInvalid() && feedback_type != static_type) {
570 os << ", Feedback type: " << feedback_type;
571 }
572 os << "]";
573 }
574 os << std::endl;
575 }
576
577 Type Weaken(Node* node, Type previous_type, Type current_type) {
578 // If the types have nothing to do with integers, return the types.
579 Type const integer = type_cache_->kInteger;
580 if (!previous_type.Maybe(integer)) {
581 return current_type;
582 }
583 DCHECK(current_type.Maybe(integer));
584
585 Type current_integer = Type::Intersect(current_type, integer, graph_zone());
586 DCHECK(!current_integer.IsNone());
587 Type previous_integer =
588 Type::Intersect(previous_type, integer, graph_zone());
589 DCHECK(!previous_integer.IsNone());
590
591 // Once we start weakening a node, we should always weaken.
592 if (!GetInfo(node)->weakened()) {
593 // Only weaken if there is range involved; we should converge quickly
594 // for all other types (the exception is a union of many constants,
595 // but we currently do not increase the number of constants in unions).
596 Type previous = previous_integer.GetRange();
597 Type current = current_integer.GetRange();
598 if (current.IsInvalid() || previous.IsInvalid()) {
599 return current_type;
600 }
601 // Range is involved => we are weakening.
602 GetInfo(node)->set_weakened();
603 }
604
605 return Type::Union(current_type,
606 op_typer_.WeakenRange(previous_integer, current_integer),
607 graph_zone());
608 }
609
610 // Generates a pre-order traversal of the nodes, starting with End.
611 void GenerateTraversal() {
612 // Reset previous state.
613 ResetNodeInfoState();
614 traversal_nodes_.clear();
615 count_ = graph()->NodeCount();
616 info_.resize(count_);
617
618 ZoneStack<NodeState> stack(zone_);
619
620 stack.push({graph()->end(), 0});
621 GetInfo(graph()->end())->set_pushed();
622 while (!stack.empty()) {
623 NodeState& current = stack.top();
624 Node* node = current.node;
625 // If there is an unvisited input, push it and continue with that node.
626 bool pushed_unvisited = false;
627 while (current.input_index < node->InputCount()) {
628 Node* input = node->InputAt(current.input_index);
629 NodeInfo* input_info = GetInfo(input);
630 current.input_index++;
631 if (input_info->unvisited()) {
632 input_info->set_pushed();
633 stack.push({input, 0});
634 pushed_unvisited = true;
635 break;
636 } else if (input_info->pushed()) {
637 // Optimization for the Retype phase.
638 // If we had already pushed (and not visited) an input, it means that
639 // the current node will be visited in the Retype phase before one of
640 // its inputs. If this happens, the current node might need to be
641 // revisited.
642 MarkAsPossibleRevisit(node, input);
643 }
644 }
645
646 if (pushed_unvisited) continue;
647
648 stack.pop();
649 NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node);
650 info->set_visited();
651
652 // Generate the traversal
653 traversal_nodes_.push_back(node);
654 }
655 }
656
657 void PushNodeToRevisitIfVisited(Node* node) {
658 NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node);
659 if (info->visited()) {
660 TRACE(" QUEUEING #%d: %s\n", node->id(), node->op()->mnemonic());
661 info->set_queued();
662 revisit_queue_.push(node);
663 }
664 }
665
666 // Tries to update the feedback type of the node, as well as setting its
667 // machine representation (in VisitNode). Returns true iff updating the
668 // feedback type is successful.
669 bool RetypeNode(Node* node) {
670 NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node);
671 info->set_visited();
672 bool updated = UpdateFeedbackType(node);
673 TRACE(" visit #%d: %s\n", node->id(), node->op()->mnemonic());
674 VisitNode<RETYPE>(node, info->truncation(), nullptr);
675 TRACE(" ==> output %s\n", MachineReprToString(info->representation()));
676 return updated;
677 }
678
679 // Visits the node and marks it as visited. Inside of VisitNode, we might
680 // change the truncation of one of our inputs (see EnqueueInput<PROPAGATE> for
681 // this). If we change the truncation of an already visited node, we will add
682 // it to the revisit queue.
683 void PropagateTruncation(Node* node) {
684 NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node);
685 info->set_visited();
686 TRACE(" visit #%d: %s (trunc: %s)\n", node->id(), node->op()->mnemonic(),
687 info->truncation().description());
688 VisitNode<PROPAGATE>(node, info->truncation(), nullptr);
689 }
690
691 // Backward propagation of truncations to a fixpoint.
692 void RunPropagatePhase() {
693 TRACE("--{Propagate phase}--\n");
694 ResetNodeInfoState();
695 DCHECK(revisit_queue_.empty());
696
697 // Process nodes in reverse post order, with End as the root.
698 for (auto it = traversal_nodes_.crbegin(); it != traversal_nodes_.crend();
699 ++it) {
700 PropagateTruncation(*it);
701
702 while (!revisit_queue_.empty()) {
703 Node* node = revisit_queue_.front();
704 revisit_queue_.pop();
705 PropagateTruncation(node);
706 }
707 }
708 }
709
710 // Forward propagation of types from type feedback to a fixpoint.
711 void RunRetypePhase() {
712 TRACE("--{Retype phase}--\n");
713 ResetNodeInfoState();
714 DCHECK(revisit_queue_.empty());
715
716 for (auto it = traversal_nodes_.cbegin(); it != traversal_nodes_.cend();
717 ++it) {
718 Node* node = *it;
719 if (!RetypeNode(node)) continue;
720
721 auto revisit_it = might_need_revisit_.find(node);
722 if (revisit_it == might_need_revisit_.end()) continue;
723
724 for (Node* const user : revisit_it->second) {
725 PushNodeToRevisitIfVisited(user);
726 }
727
728 // Process the revisit queue.
729 while (!revisit_queue_.empty()) {
730 Node* revisit_node = revisit_queue_.front();
731 revisit_queue_.pop();
732 if (!RetypeNode(revisit_node)) continue;
733 // Here we need to check all uses since we can't easily know which
734 // nodes will need to be revisited due to having an input which was
735 // a revisited node.
736 for (Node* const user : revisit_node->uses()) {
737 PushNodeToRevisitIfVisited(user);
738 }
739 }
740 }
741 }
742
743 // Lowering and change insertion phase.
744 void RunLowerPhase(SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
745 TRACE("--{Lower phase}--\n");
746 for (auto it = traversal_nodes_.cbegin(); it != traversal_nodes_.cend();
747 ++it) {
748 Node* node = *it;
749 NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node);
750 TRACE(" visit #%d: %s\n", node->id(), node->op()->mnemonic());
751 // Reuse {VisitNode()} so the representation rules are in one place.
752 SourcePositionTable::Scope scope(
753 source_positions_, source_positions_->GetSourcePosition(node));
754 NodeOriginTable::Scope origin_scope(node_origins_, "simplified lowering",
755 node);
756 VisitNode<LOWER>(node, info->truncation(), lowering);
757 }
758
759 // Perform the final replacements.
760 for (NodeVector::iterator i = replacements_.begin();
761 i != replacements_.end(); ++i) {
762 Node* node = *i;
763 Node* replacement = *(++i);
764 node->ReplaceUses(replacement);
765 node->Kill();
766 // We also need to replace the node in the rest of the vector.
767 for (NodeVector::iterator j = i + 1; j != replacements_.end(); ++j) {
768 ++j;
769 if (*j == node) *j = replacement;
770 }
771 }
772 }
773
774 void RunVerifyPhase(OptimizedCompilationInfo* compilation_info) {
775 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(verifier_);
776
777 TRACE("--{Verify Phase}--\n");
778
779 // Patch pending type overrides.
780 for (const auto& [constant, uses] :
781 verifier_->machine_uses_of_constants()) {
782 Node* typed_constant =
783 InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(Type::Machine(), constant);
784 for (auto use : uses) {
785 for (int i = 0; i < use->InputCount(); ++i) {
786 if (use->InputAt(i) == constant) {
787 use->ReplaceInput(i, typed_constant);
788 }
789 }
790 }
791 }
792
793 // Generate a new traversal containing all the new nodes created during
794 // lowering.
795 GenerateTraversal();
796
797 // Set node types to the refined types computed during retyping.
798 for (Node* node : traversal_nodes_) {
799 NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node);
800 if (!info->feedback_type().IsInvalid()) {
801 NodeProperties::SetType(node, info->feedback_type());
802 }
803 }
804
805 // Print graph.
806 if (compilation_info != nullptr && compilation_info->trace_turbo_json()) {
807 UnparkedScopeIfNeeded scope(broker_);
808 AllowHandleDereference allow_deref;
809
810 TurboJsonFile json_of(compilation_info, std::ios_base::app);
811 JSONGraphWriter writer(json_of, graph(), source_positions_,
812 node_origins_);
813 writer.PrintPhase("V8.TFSimplifiedLowering [after lower]");
814 }
815
816 // Verify all nodes.
817 for (Node* node : traversal_nodes_) {
818 verifier_->VisitNode(node, op_typer_);
819 }
820
821 // Print graph.
822 if (compilation_info != nullptr && compilation_info->trace_turbo_json()) {
823 UnparkedScopeIfNeeded scope(broker_);
824 AllowHandleDereference allow_deref;
825
826 TurboJsonFile json_of(compilation_info, std::ios_base::app);
827 JSONGraphWriterWithVerifierTypes writer(
828 json_of, graph(), source_positions_, node_origins_, verifier_);
829 writer.PrintPhase("V8.TFSimplifiedLowering [after verify]");
830 }
831
832 // Eliminate all introduced hints.
833 for (Node* node : verifier_->inserted_hints()) {
834 Node* input = node->InputAt(0);
835 node->ReplaceUses(input);
836 node->Kill();
837 }
838 }
839
840 void Run(SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
841 GenerateTraversal();
842 RunPropagatePhase();
843 RunRetypePhase();
844 RunLowerPhase(lowering);
845 if (verification_enabled()) {
846 RunVerifyPhase(lowering->info_);
847 }
848 }
849
850 // Just assert for Retype and Lower. Propagate specialized below.
851 template <Phase T>
852 void EnqueueInput(Node* use_node, int index,
853 UseInfo use_info = UseInfo::None()) {
854 static_assert(retype<T>() || lower<T>(),
855 "This version of EnqueueInput has to be called in "
856 "the Retype or Lower phase.");
857 }
858
859 template <Phase T>
860 static constexpr bool propagate() {
861 return T == PROPAGATE;
862 }
863
864 template <Phase T>
865 static constexpr bool retype() {
866 return T == RETYPE;
867 }
868
869 template <Phase T>
870 static constexpr bool lower() {
871 return T == LOWER;
872 }
873
874 template <Phase T>
875 void SetOutput(Node* node, MachineRepresentation representation,
876 Type restriction_type = Type::Any());
877
878 Type GetUpperBound(Node* node) { return NodeProperties::GetType(node); }
879
880 bool InputCannotBe(Node* node, Type type) {
881 DCHECK_EQ(1, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
882 return !GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0)).Maybe(type);
883 }
884
885 bool InputIs(Node* node, Type type) {
886 DCHECK_EQ(1, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
887 return GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0)).Is(type);
888 }
889
890 bool BothInputsAreSigned32(Node* node) {
891 return BothInputsAre(node, Type::Signed32());
892 }
893
894 bool BothInputsAreUnsigned32(Node* node) {
895 return BothInputsAre(node, Type::Unsigned32());
896 }
897
898 bool BothInputsAre(Node* node, Type type) {
899 DCHECK_EQ(2, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
900 return GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0)).Is(type) &&
901 GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1)).Is(type);
902 }
903
904 bool IsNodeRepresentationTagged(Node* node) {
905 MachineRepresentation representation = GetInfo(node)->representation();
906 return IsAnyTagged(representation);
907 }
908
909 bool OneInputCannotBe(Node* node, Type type) {
910 DCHECK_EQ(2, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
911 return !GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0)).Maybe(type) ||
912 !GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1)).Maybe(type);
913 }
914
915 void ChangeToDeadValue(Node* node, Node* effect, Node* control) {
916 DCHECK(TypeOf(node).IsNone());
917 // If the node is unreachable, insert an Unreachable node and mark the
918 // value dead.
919 // TODO(jarin,turbofan) Find a way to unify/merge this insertion with
920 // InsertUnreachableIfNecessary.
921 Node* unreachable = effect =
922 graph()->NewNode(common()->Unreachable(), effect, control);
923 const Operator* dead_value =
924 common()->DeadValue(GetInfo(node)->representation());
925 node->ReplaceInput(0, unreachable);
926 node->TrimInputCount(dead_value->ValueInputCount());
927 ReplaceEffectControlUses(node, effect, control);
928 ChangeOp(node, dead_value);
929 }
930
931 // This function is a generalization of ChangeToPureOp. It can be used to
932 // replace a node that is part of the effect and control chain by a pure node.
933 void ReplaceWithPureNode(Node* node, Node* pure_node) {
934 DCHECK(pure_node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kPure));
935 if (node->op()->EffectInputCount() > 0) {
936 DCHECK_LT(0, node->op()->ControlInputCount());
937 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
938 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
939 if (TypeOf(node).IsNone()) {
940 ChangeToDeadValue(node, effect, control);
941 return;
942 }
943 // Rewire the effect and control chains.
944 ReplaceEffectControlUses(node, effect, control);
945 } else {
946 DCHECK_EQ(0, node->op()->ControlInputCount());
947 }
948 DeferReplacement(node, pure_node);
949 }
950
951 void ChangeToPureOp(Node* node, const Operator* new_op) {
952 DCHECK(new_op->HasProperty(Operator::kPure));
953 DCHECK_EQ(new_op->ValueInputCount(), node->op()->ValueInputCount());
954 if (node->op()->EffectInputCount() > 0) {
955 DCHECK_LT(0, node->op()->ControlInputCount());
956 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
957 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
958 if (TypeOf(node).IsNone()) {
959 ChangeToDeadValue(node, effect, control);
960 return;
961 }
962 // Rewire the effect and control chains.
963 node->TrimInputCount(new_op->ValueInputCount());
964 ReplaceEffectControlUses(node, effect, control);
965 } else {
966 DCHECK_EQ(0, node->op()->ControlInputCount());
967 }
968 ChangeOp(node, new_op);
969 }
970
971 void ChangeUnaryToPureBinaryOp(Node* node, const Operator* new_op,
972 int new_input_index, Node* new_input) {
973 DCHECK(new_op->HasProperty(Operator::kPure));
974 DCHECK_EQ(new_op->ValueInputCount(), 2);
975 DCHECK_EQ(node->op()->ValueInputCount(), 1);
976 DCHECK_LE(0, new_input_index);
977 DCHECK_LE(new_input_index, 1);
978 if (node->op()->EffectInputCount() > 0) {
979 DCHECK_LT(0, node->op()->ControlInputCount());
980 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
981 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
982 if (TypeOf(node).IsNone()) {
983 ChangeToDeadValue(node, effect, control);
984 return;
985 }
986 node->TrimInputCount(node->op()->ValueInputCount());
987 ReplaceEffectControlUses(node, effect, control);
988 } else {
989 DCHECK_EQ(0, node->op()->ControlInputCount());
990 }
991 if (new_input_index == 0) {
992 node->InsertInput(jsgraph_->zone(), 0, new_input);
993 } else {
994 DCHECK_EQ(new_input_index, 1);
995 DCHECK_EQ(node->InputCount(), 1);
996 node->AppendInput(jsgraph_->zone(), new_input);
997 }
998 ChangeOp(node, new_op);
999 }
1000
1001 // Converts input {index} of {node} according to given UseInfo {use},
1002 // assuming the type of the input is {input_type}. If {input_type} is null,
1003 // it takes the input from the input node {TypeOf(node->InputAt(index))}.
1004 void ConvertInput(Node* node, int index, UseInfo use,
1005 Type input_type = Type::Invalid()) {
1006 // In the change phase, insert a change before the use if necessary.
1007 if (use.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kNone)
1008 return; // No input requirement on the use.
1009 Node* input = node->InputAt(index);
1010 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(input);
1011 NodeInfo* input_info = GetInfo(input);
1012 MachineRepresentation input_rep = input_info->representation();
1013 if (input_rep != use.representation() ||
1014 use.type_check() != TypeCheckKind::kNone) {
1015 // Output representation doesn't match usage.
1016 TRACE(" change: #%d:%s(@%d #%d:%s) ", node->id(), node->op()->mnemonic(),
1017 index, input->id(), input->op()->mnemonic());
1018 TRACE("from %s to %s:%s\n",
1019 MachineReprToString(input_info->representation()),
1020 MachineReprToString(use.representation()),
1021 use.truncation().description());
1022 if (input_type.IsInvalid()) {
1023 input_type = TypeOf(input);
1024 } else {
1025 // This case is reached when ConvertInput is called for TypeGuard nodes
1026 // which explicitly set the {input_type} for their input. In order to
1027 // correctly verify the resulting graph, we have to preserve this
1028 // forced type for the verifier.
1029 DCHECK_EQ(node->opcode(), IrOpcode::kTypeGuard);
1030 input = InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(input_type, input);
1031 }
1032 Node* n = changer_->GetRepresentationFor(input, input_rep, input_type,
1033 node, use);
1034 node->ReplaceInput(index, n);
1035 }
1036 }
1037
1038 template <Phase T>
1039 void ProcessInput(Node* node, int index, UseInfo use);
1040
1041 // Just assert for Retype and Lower. Propagate specialized below.
1042 template <Phase T>
1043 void ProcessRemainingInputs(Node* node, int index) {
1044 static_assert(retype<T>() || lower<T>(),
1045 "This version of ProcessRemainingInputs has to be called in "
1046 "the Retype or Lower phase.");
1047 DCHECK_GE(index, NodeProperties::PastValueIndex(node));
1048 DCHECK_GE(index, NodeProperties::PastContextIndex(node));
1049 }
1050
1051 // Marks node as a possible revisit since it is a use of input that will be
1052 // visited before input is visited.
1053 void MarkAsPossibleRevisit(Node* node, Node* input) {
1054 auto it = might_need_revisit_.find(input);
1055 if (it == might_need_revisit_.end()) {
1056 it = might_need_revisit_.insert({input, ZoneVector<Node*>(zone())}).first;
1057 }
1058 it->second.push_back(node);
1059 TRACE(" Marking #%d: %s as needing revisit due to #%d: %s\n", node->id(),
1060 node->op()->mnemonic(), input->id(), input->op()->mnemonic());
1061 }
1062
1063 // Just assert for Retype. Propagate and Lower specialized below.
1064 template <Phase T>
1065 void VisitInputs(Node* node) {
1066 static_assert(
1067 retype<T>(),
1068 "This version of VisitInputs has to be called in the Retype phase.");
1069 }
1070
1071 template <Phase T>
1072 void VisitReturn(Node* node) {
1073 int first_effect_index = NodeProperties::FirstEffectIndex(node);
1074 // Visit integer slot count to pop
1075 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32());
1076
1077 // Visit value, context and frame state inputs as tagged.
1078 for (int i = 1; i < first_effect_index; i++) {
1079 ProcessInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1080 }
1081 // Only enqueue other inputs (effects, control).
1082 for (int i = first_effect_index; i < node->InputCount(); i++) {
1083 EnqueueInput<T>(node, i);
1084 }
1085 }
1086
1087 // Helper for an unused node.
1088 template <Phase T>
1089 void VisitUnused(Node* node) {
1090 int first_effect_index = NodeProperties::FirstEffectIndex(node);
1091 for (int i = 0; i < first_effect_index; i++) {
1092 ProcessInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::None());
1093 }
1094 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, first_effect_index);
1095
1096 if (lower<T>()) {
1097 TRACE("disconnecting unused #%d:%s\n", node->id(),
1098 node->op()->mnemonic());
1099 DisconnectFromEffectAndControl(node);
1100 node->NullAllInputs(); // Node is now dead.
1101 DeferReplacement(node, graph()->NewNode(common()->Plug()));
1102 }
1103 }
1104
1105 // Helper for no-op node.
1106 template <Phase T>
1107 void VisitNoop(Node* node, Truncation truncation) {
1108 if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
1109 MachineRepresentation representation =
1110 GetOutputInfoForPhi(TypeOf(node), truncation);
1111 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo(representation, truncation), representation);
1112 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
1113 }
1114
1115 // Helper for binops of the R x L -> O variety.
1116 template <Phase T>
1117 void VisitBinop(Node* node, UseInfo left_use, UseInfo right_use,
1118 MachineRepresentation output,
1119 Type restriction_type = Type::Any()) {
1120 DCHECK_EQ(2, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
1121 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, left_use);
1122 ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, right_use);
1123 for (int i = 2; i < node->InputCount(); i++) {
1124 EnqueueInput<T>(node, i);
1125 }
1126 SetOutput<T>(node, output, restriction_type);
1127 }
1128
1129 // Helper for binops of the I x I -> O variety.
1130 template <Phase T>
1131 void VisitBinop(Node* node, UseInfo input_use, MachineRepresentation output,
1132 Type restriction_type = Type::Any()) {
1133 VisitBinop<T>(node, input_use, input_use, output, restriction_type);
1134 }
1135
1136 template <Phase T>
1137 void VisitSpeculativeInt32Binop(Node* node) {
1138 DCHECK_EQ(2, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
1139 if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::NumberOrOddball())) {
1140 return VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
1141 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1142 }
1143 NumberOperationHint hint = NumberOperationHintOf(node->op());
1144 return VisitBinop<T>(node,
1145 CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros),
1146 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1147 }
1148
1149 // Helper for unops of the I -> O variety.
1150 template <Phase T>
1151 void VisitUnop(Node* node, UseInfo input_use, MachineRepresentation output,
1152 Type restriction_type = Type::Any()) {
1153 DCHECK_EQ(1, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
1154 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, input_use);
1155 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 1);
1156 SetOutput<T>(node, output, restriction_type);
1157 }
1158
1159 // Helper for leaf nodes.
1160 template <Phase T>
1161 void VisitLeaf(Node* node, MachineRepresentation output) {
1162 DCHECK_EQ(0, node->InputCount());
1163 SetOutput<T>(node, output);
1164 }

1166 // Helpers for specific types of binops.
1167
1168 template <Phase T>
1169 void VisitFloat64Binop(Node* node) {
1170 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
1171 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
1172 }
1173
1174 template <Phase T>
1175 void VisitInt64Binop(Node* node) {
1176 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::Word64(), MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
1177 }
1178
1179 template <Phase T>
1180 void VisitWord32TruncatingBinop(Node* node) {
1181 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
1182 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1183 }
1184
1185 // Infer representation for phi-like nodes.
1186 MachineRepresentation GetOutputInfoForPhi(Type type, Truncation use) {
1187 // Compute the representation.
1188 if (type.Is(Type::None())) {
1189 return MachineRepresentation::kNone;
1190 } else if (type.Is(Type::Signed32()) || type.Is(Type::Unsigned32())) {
1191 return MachineRepresentation::kWord32;
1192 } else if (type.Is(Type::NumberOrOddball()) && use.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
1193 return MachineRepresentation::kWord32;
1194 } else if (type.Is(Type::Boolean())) {
1195 return MachineRepresentation::kBit;
1196 } else if (type.Is(Type::NumberOrOddball()) &&
1197 use.TruncatesOddballAndBigIntToNumber()) {
1198 return MachineRepresentation::kFloat64;
1199 } else if (type.Is(Type::Union(Type::SignedSmall(), Type::NaN(), zone()))) {
1200 // TODO(turbofan): For Phis that return either NaN or some Smi, it's
1201 // beneficial to not go all the way to double, unless the uses are
1202 // double uses. For tagging that just means some potentially expensive
1203 // allocation code; we might want to do the same for -0 as well?
1204 return MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
1205 } else if (type.Is(Type::Number())) {
1206 return MachineRepresentation::kFloat64;
1207 } else if (type.Is(Type::BigInt()) && Is64() && use.IsUsedAsWord64()) {
1208 return MachineRepresentation::kWord64;
1209 } else if (type.Is(Type::ExternalPointer()) ||
1210 type.Is(Type::SandboxedPointer())) {
1211 return MachineType::PointerRepresentation();
1212 }
1213 return MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
1214 }
1215
1216 // Helper for handling selects.
1217 template <Phase T>
1218 void VisitSelect(Node* node, Truncation truncation,
1219 SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1220 DCHECK(TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Boolean()));
1221 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Bool());
1222
1223 MachineRepresentation output =
1224 GetOutputInfoForPhi(TypeOf(node), truncation);
1225 SetOutput<T>(node, output);
1226
1227 if (lower<T>()) {
1228 // Update the select operator.
1229 SelectParameters p = SelectParametersOf(node->op());
1230 if (output != p.representation()) {
1231 ChangeOp(node, lowering->common()->Select(output, p.hint()));
1232 }
1233 }
1234 // Convert inputs to the output representation of this phi, pass the
1235 // truncation truncation along.
1236 UseInfo input_use(output, truncation);
1237 ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, input_use);
1238 ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, input_use);
1239 }
1240
1241 // Helper for handling phis.
1242 template <Phase T>
1243 void VisitPhi(Node* node, Truncation truncation,
1244 SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1245 // If we already have a non-tagged representation set in the Phi node, it
1246 // does come from subgraphs using machine operators we introduced early in
1247 // the pipeline. In this case, we just keep the representation.
1248 MachineRepresentation output = PhiRepresentationOf(node->op());
1249 if (output == MachineRepresentation::kTagged) {
1250 output = GetOutputInfoForPhi(TypeOf(node), truncation);
1251 }
1252 // Only set the output representation if not running with type
1253 // feedback. (Feedback typing will set the representation.)
1254 SetOutput<T>(node, output);
1255
1256 int values = node->op()->ValueInputCount();
1257 if (lower<T>()) {
1258 // Update the phi operator.
1259 if (output != PhiRepresentationOf(node->op())) {
1260 ChangeOp(node, lowering->common()->Phi(output, values));
1261 }
1262 }
1263
1264 // Convert inputs to the output representation of this phi, pass the
1265 // truncation along.
1266 UseInfo input_use(output, truncation);
1267 for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCount(); i++) {
1268 ProcessInput<T>(node, i, i < values ? input_use : UseInfo::None());
1269 }
1270 }
1271
1272 template <Phase T>
1273 void VisitObjectIs(Node* node, Type type, SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1274 Type const input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
1275 if (input_type.Is(type)) {
1276 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::None(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
1277 if (lower<T>()) {
1278 DeferReplacement(
1279 node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
1280 true_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(1)));
1281 }
1282 } else {
1283 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
1284 if (lower<T>() && !input_type.Maybe(type)) {
1285 DeferReplacement(
1286 node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
1287 false_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0)));
1288 }
1289 }
1290 }
1291
1292 template <Phase T>
1293 void VisitCheck(Node* node, Type type, SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1294 if (InputIs(node, type)) {
1295 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
1296 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
1297 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
1298 } else {
1299 VisitUnop<T>(node,
1300 UseInfo::CheckedHeapObjectAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource()),
1301 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
1302 }
1303 }
1304
1305 template <Phase T>
1306 void VisitCall(Node* node, SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1307 auto call_descriptor = CallDescriptorOf(node->op());
1308 int params = static_cast<int>(call_descriptor->ParameterCount());
1309 int value_input_count = node->op()->ValueInputCount();
1310
1311 DCHECK_GT(value_input_count, 0);
1312 DCHECK_GE(value_input_count, params);
1313
1314 // The target of the call.
1315 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Any());
1316
1317 // For the parameters (indexes [1, ..., params]), propagate representation
1318 // information from call descriptor.
1319 for (int i = 1; i <= params; i++) {
1320 ProcessInput<T>(node, i,
1321 TruncatingUseInfoFromRepresentation(
1322 call_descriptor->GetInputType(i).representation()));
1323 }
1324
1325 // Rest of the value inputs.
1326 for (int i = params + 1; i < value_input_count; i++) {
1327 ProcessInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1328 }
1329
1330 // Effect and Control.
1331 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, value_input_count);
1332
1333 if (call_descriptor->ReturnCount() > 0) {
1334 SetOutput<T>(node, call_descriptor->GetReturnType(0).representation());
1335 } else {
1336 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1337 }
1338 }
1339
1340 void MaskShiftOperand(Node* node, Type rhs_type) {
1341 if (!rhs_type.Is(type_cache_->kZeroToThirtyOne)) {
1342 Node* const rhs = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
1343 node->ReplaceInput(1,
1344 graph()->NewNode(jsgraph_->machine()->Word32And(), rhs,
1345 jsgraph_->Int32Constant(0x1F)));
1346 }
1347 }
1348
1349 static MachineSemantic DeoptValueSemanticOf(Type type) {
1350 // We only need signedness to do deopt correctly.
1351 if (type.Is(Type::Signed32())) {
1352 return MachineSemantic::kInt32;
1353 } else if (type.Is(Type::Unsigned32())) {
1354 return MachineSemantic::kUint32;
1355 } else {
1356 return MachineSemantic::kAny;
1357 }
1358 }
1359
1360 static MachineType DeoptMachineTypeOf(MachineRepresentation rep, Type type) {
1361 if (type.IsNone()) {
1362 return MachineType::None();
1363 }
1364 // Do not distinguish between various Tagged variations.
1365 if (IsAnyTagged(rep)) {
1366 return MachineType::AnyTagged();
1367 }
1368 if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kWord64) {
1369 if (type.Is(Type::SignedBigInt64())) {
1370 return MachineType::SignedBigInt64();
1371 }
1372
1373 if (type.Is(Type::UnsignedBigInt64())) {
1374 return MachineType::UnsignedBigInt64();
1375 }
1376
1377 if (type.Is(Type::BigInt())) {
1378 return MachineType::AnyTagged();
1379 }
1380
1381 DCHECK(type.Is(TypeCache::Get()->kSafeInteger));
1382 return MachineType(rep, MachineSemantic::kInt64);
1383 }
1384 MachineType machine_type(rep, DeoptValueSemanticOf(type));
1385 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
1386 machine_type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kWord32,
1387 machine_type.semantic() == MachineSemantic::kInt32 ||
1388 machine_type.semantic() == MachineSemantic::kUint32);
1389 DCHECK_IMPLIES(machine_type.representation() == MachineRepresentation::kBit,
1390 type.Is(Type::Boolean()));
1391 return machine_type;
1392 }
1393
1394 template <Phase T>
1395 void VisitStateValues(Node* node) {
1396 if (propagate<T>()) {
1397 for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCount(); i++) {
1398 // BigInt64s are rematerialized in deoptimization. The other BigInts
1399 // must be rematerialized before deoptimization. By propagating an
1400 // AnyTagged use, the RepresentationChanger is going to insert the
1401 // necessary conversions.
1402 if (IsLargeBigInt(TypeOf(node->InputAt(i)))) {
1403 EnqueueInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1404 } else {
1405 EnqueueInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::Any());
1406 }
1407 }
1408 } else if (lower<T>()) {
1409 Zone* zone = jsgraph_->zone();
1410 ZoneVector<MachineType>* types =
1411 zone->New<ZoneVector<MachineType>>(node->InputCount(), zone);
1412 for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCount(); i++) {
1413 Node* input = node->InputAt(i);
1414 if (IsLargeBigInt(TypeOf(input))) {
1415 ConvertInput(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1416 }
1417
1418 (*types)[i] =
1419 DeoptMachineTypeOf(GetInfo(input)->representation(), TypeOf(input));
1420 }
1421 SparseInputMask mask = SparseInputMaskOf(node->op());
1422 ChangeOp(node, common()->TypedStateValues(types, mask));
1423 }
1424 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1425 }
1426
1427 template <Phase T>
1428 void VisitFrameState(FrameState node) {
1429 DCHECK_EQ(5, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
1430 DCHECK_EQ(1, OperatorProperties::GetFrameStateInputCount(node->op()));
1431 DCHECK_EQ(FrameState::kFrameStateInputCount, node->InputCount());
1432
1433 ProcessInput<T>(node, FrameState::kFrameStateParametersInput,
1434 UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1435 ProcessInput<T>(node, FrameState::kFrameStateLocalsInput,
1436 UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1437
1438 // Accumulator is a special flower - we need to remember its type in
1439 // a singleton typed-state-values node (as if it was a singleton
1440 // state-values node).
1441 Node* accumulator = node.stack();
1442 if (propagate<T>()) {
1443 if (IsLargeBigInt(TypeOf(accumulator))) {
1444 EnqueueInput<T>(node, FrameState::kFrameStateStackInput,
1445 UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1446 } else {
1447 EnqueueInput<T>(node, FrameState::kFrameStateStackInput,
1448 UseInfo::Any());
1449 }
1450 } else if (lower<T>()) {
1451 if (IsLargeBigInt(TypeOf(accumulator))) {
1452 ConvertInput(node, FrameState::kFrameStateStackInput,
1453 UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1454 accumulator = node.stack();
1455 }
1456 Zone* zone = jsgraph_->zone();
1457 if (accumulator == jsgraph_->OptimizedOutConstant()) {
1458 node->ReplaceInput(FrameState::kFrameStateStackInput,
1459 jsgraph_->SingleDeadTypedStateValues());
1460 } else {
1461 ZoneVector<MachineType>* types =
1462 zone->New<ZoneVector<MachineType>>(1, zone);
1463 (*types)[0] = DeoptMachineTypeOf(GetInfo(accumulator)->representation(),
1464 TypeOf(accumulator));
1465
1466 node->ReplaceInput(
1467 FrameState::kFrameStateStackInput,
1468 jsgraph_->graph()->NewNode(
1469 common()->TypedStateValues(types, SparseInputMask::Dense()),
1470 node.stack()));
1471 }
1472 }
1473
1474 ProcessInput<T>(node, FrameState::kFrameStateContextInput,
1475 UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1476 ProcessInput<T>(node, FrameState::kFrameStateFunctionInput,
1477 UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1478 ProcessInput<T>(node, FrameState::kFrameStateOuterStateInput,
1479 UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1480 return SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1481 }
1482
1483 template <Phase T>
1484 void VisitObjectState(Node* node) {
1485 if (propagate<T>()) {
1486 for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCount(); i++) {
1487 if (IsLargeBigInt(TypeOf(node->InputAt(i)))) {
1488 EnqueueInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1489 } else {
1490 EnqueueInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::Any());
1491 }
1492 }
1493 } else if (lower<T>()) {
1494 Zone* zone = jsgraph_->zone();
1495 ZoneVector<MachineType>* types =
1496 zone->New<ZoneVector<MachineType>>(node->InputCount(), zone);
1497 for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCount(); i++) {
1498 Node* input = node->InputAt(i);
1499 (*types)[i] =
1500 DeoptMachineTypeOf(GetInfo(input)->representation(), TypeOf(input));
1501 if (IsLargeBigInt(TypeOf(input))) {
1502 ConvertInput(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
1503 }
1504 }
1505 ChangeOp(node, common()->TypedObjectState(ObjectIdOf(node->op()), types));
1506 }
1507 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
1508 }

1515 return changer_->Int32OverflowOperatorFor(node->opcode());
1516 }

1518 const Operator* Int64Op(Node* node) {
1519 return changer_->Int64OperatorFor(node->opcode());
1520 }

1523 return changer_->Int64OverflowOperatorFor(node->opcode());
1524 }

1527 return changer_->BigIntOperatorFor(node->opcode());
1528 }
1529
1530 const Operator* Uint32Op(Node* node) {
1531 return changer_->Uint32OperatorFor(node->opcode());
1532 }
1533
1534 const Operator* Uint32OverflowOp(Node* node) {
1535 return changer_->Uint32OverflowOperatorFor(node->opcode());
