1539 return changer_->Float64OperatorFor(node->opcode());
1540 }
1541
1542 WriteBarrierKind WriteBarrierKindFor(
1543 BaseTaggedness base_taggedness,
1544 MachineRepresentation field_representation, Type field_type,
1545 MachineRepresentation value_representation, Node* value) {
1546 if (base_taggedness == kTaggedBase &&
1547 CanBeTaggedPointer(field_representation)) {
1548 Type value_type = NodeProperties::GetType(value);
1549 if (value_representation == MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned) {
1550 // Write barriers are only for stores of heap objects.
1551 return kNoWriteBarrier;
1552 }
1553 if (field_type.Is(Type::BooleanOrNullOrUndefined()) ||
1554 value_type.Is(Type::BooleanOrNullOrUndefined())) {
1555 // Write barriers are not necessary when storing true, false, null or
1556 // undefined, because these special oddballs are always in the root set.
1557 return kNoWriteBarrier;
1558 }
1559 if (value_type.IsHeapConstant()) {
1560 RootIndex root_index;
1561 const RootsTable& roots_table = jsgraph_->isolate()->roots_table();
1562 if (roots_table.IsRootHandle(value_type.AsHeapConstant()->Value(),
1563 &root_index)) {
1564 if (RootsTable::IsImmortalImmovable(root_index)) {
1565 // Write barriers are unnecessary for immortal immovable roots.
1566 return kNoWriteBarrier;
1567 }
1568 }
1569 }
1570 if (field_representation == MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer ||
1571 value_representation == MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer) {
1572 // Write barriers for heap objects are cheaper.
1573 return kPointerWriteBarrier;
1574 }
1575 NumberMatcher m(value);
1576 if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
1577 if (IsSmiDouble(m.ResolvedValue())) {
1578 // Storing a smi doesn't need a write barrier.
1579 return kNoWriteBarrier;
1580 }
1581 // The NumberConstant will be represented as HeapNumber.
1582 return kPointerWriteBarrier;
1583 }
1584 return kFullWriteBarrier;
1585 }
1586 return kNoWriteBarrier;
1587 }
1588
1589 WriteBarrierKind WriteBarrierKindFor(
1590 BaseTaggedness base_taggedness,
1591 MachineRepresentation field_representation, int field_offset,
1592 Type field_type, MachineRepresentation value_representation,
1593 Node* value) {
1594 WriteBarrierKind write_barrier_kind =
1595 WriteBarrierKindFor(base_taggedness, field_representation, field_type,
1596 value_representation, value);
1597 if (write_barrier_kind != kNoWriteBarrier) {
1598 if (base_taggedness == kTaggedBase &&
1599 field_offset == HeapObject::kMapOffset) {
1600 write_barrier_kind = kMapWriteBarrier;
1601 }
1602 }
1603 return write_barrier_kind;
1604 }
1605
1606 Graph* graph() const { return jsgraph_->graph(); }
1607 CommonOperatorBuilder* common() const { return jsgraph_->common(); }
1608 SimplifiedOperatorBuilder* simplified() const {
1609 return jsgraph_->simplified();
1610 }
1611
1612 template <Phase T>
1613 void VisitForCheckedInt32Mul(Node* node, Truncation truncation,
1614 Type input0_type, Type input1_type,
1615 UseInfo input_use) {
1616 DCHECK_EQ(node->opcode(), IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberMultiply);
1617 // A -0 input is impossible or will cause a deopt.
1618 DCHECK(BothInputsAre(node, Type::Signed32()) ||
1619 !input_use.truncation().IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero());
1620
1621 CheckForMinusZeroMode mz_mode;
1622 Type restriction;
1623 if (IsSomePositiveOrderedNumber(input0_type) ||
1624 IsSomePositiveOrderedNumber(input1_type)) {
1625 mz_mode = CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero;
1626 restriction = Type::Signed32();
1627 } else if (truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero()) {
1628 mz_mode = CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero;
1629 restriction = Type::Signed32OrMinusZero();
1630 } else {
1631 mz_mode = CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero;
1632 restriction = Type::Signed32();
1633 }
1634
1635 VisitBinop<T>(node, input_use, MachineRepresentation::kWord32, restriction);
1636 if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, simplified()->CheckedInt32Mul(mz_mode));
1637 }
1638
1639 void ChangeToInt32OverflowOp(Node* node) {
1640 ChangeOp(node, Int32OverflowOp(node));
1641 }
1642
1643 void ChangeToUint32OverflowOp(Node* node) {
1644 ChangeOp(node, Uint32OverflowOp(node));
1645 }
1646
1647 template <Phase T>
1648 void VisitSpeculativeIntegerAdditiveOp(Node* node, Truncation truncation,
1649 SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1650 Type left_upper = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0));
1651 Type right_upper = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
1652
1653 if (left_upper.Is(type_cache_->kAdditiveSafeIntegerOrMinusZero) &&
1654 right_upper.Is(type_cache_->kAdditiveSafeIntegerOrMinusZero)) {
1655 // Only eliminate the node if its typing rule can be satisfied, namely
1656 // that a safe integer is produced.
1657 if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
1658
1659 // If we know how to interpret the result or if the users only care
1660 // about the low 32-bits, we can truncate to Word32 do a wrapping
1661 // addition.
1662 if (GetUpperBound(node).Is(Type::Signed32()) ||
1663 GetUpperBound(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) ||
1664 truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
1665 // => Int32Add/Sub
1666 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
1667 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
1668 return;
1669 }
1670 }
1671
1672 // Try to use type feedback.
1673 NumberOperationHint const hint = NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall;
1674 DCHECK_EQ(hint, NumberOperationHintOf(node->op()));
1675
1676 Type left_feedback_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
1677 Type right_feedback_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
1678
1679 // Using Signed32 as restriction type amounts to promising there won't be
1680 // signed overflow. This is incompatible with relying on a Word32 truncation
1681 // in order to skip the overflow check. Similarly, we must not drop -0 from
1682 // the result type unless we deopt for -0 inputs.
1683 Type const restriction =
1684 truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()
1685 ? Type::Any()
1686 : (truncation.identify_zeros() == kIdentifyZeros)
1687 ? Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()
1688 : Type::Signed32();
1689
1690 // Handle the case when no int32 checks on inputs are necessary (but
1691 // an overflow check is needed on the output). Note that we do not
1692 // have to do any check if at most one side can be minus zero. For
1693 // subtraction we need to handle the case of -0 - 0 properly, since
1694 // that can produce -0.
1695 Type left_constraint_type =
1696 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kSpeculativeSafeIntegerAdd
1697 ? Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()
1698 : Type::Signed32();
1699 if (left_upper.Is(left_constraint_type) &&
1700 right_upper.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) &&
1701 (left_upper.Is(Type::Signed32()) || right_upper.Is(Type::Signed32()))) {
1702 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
1703 MachineRepresentation::kWord32, restriction);
1704 } else {
1705 // If the output's truncation is identify-zeros, we can pass it
1706 // along. Moreover, if the operation is addition and we know the
1707 // right-hand side is not minus zero, we do not have to distinguish
1708 // between 0 and -0.
1709 IdentifyZeros left_identify_zeros = truncation.identify_zeros();
1710 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kSpeculativeSafeIntegerAdd &&
1711 !right_feedback_type.Maybe(Type::MinusZero())) {
1712 left_identify_zeros = kIdentifyZeros;
1713 }
1714 UseInfo left_use =
1715 CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, left_identify_zeros);
1716 // For CheckedInt32Add and CheckedInt32Sub, we don't need to do
1717 // a minus zero check for the right hand side, since we already
1718 // know that the left hand side is a proper Signed32 value,
1719 // potentially guarded by a check.
1720 UseInfo right_use = CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros);
1721 VisitBinop<T>(node, left_use, right_use, MachineRepresentation::kWord32,
1722 restriction);
1723 }
1724
1725 if (lower<T>()) {
1726 if (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() ||
1727 !CanOverflowSigned32(node->op(), left_feedback_type,
1728 right_feedback_type, type_cache_,
1729 graph_zone())) {
1730 ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
1731 } else {
1732 ChangeToInt32OverflowOp(node);
1733 }
1734 }
1735 }
1736
1737 template <Phase T>
1738 void VisitSpeculativeAdditiveOp(Node* node, Truncation truncation,
1739 SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1740 if (BothInputsAre(node, type_cache_->kAdditiveSafeIntegerOrMinusZero) &&
1741 (GetUpperBound(node).Is(Type::Signed32()) ||
1742 GetUpperBound(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) ||
1743 truncation.IsUsedAsWord32())) {
1744 // => Int32Add/Sub
1745 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
1746 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
1747 return;
1748 }
1749
1750 // default case => Float64Add/Sub
1751 VisitBinop<T>(node,
1752 UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64(kDistinguishZeros,
1753 FeedbackSource()),
1754 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, Type::Number());
1755 if (lower<T>()) {
1756 ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
1757 }
1758 }
1759
1760 template <Phase T>
1761 void VisitSpeculativeNumberModulus(Node* node, Truncation truncation,
1762 SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1763 if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZeroOrNaN()) &&
1764 (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() ||
1765 NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()))) {
1766 // => unsigned Uint32Mod
1767 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
1768 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Uint32Mod(node));
1769 return;
1770 }
1771 if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::Signed32OrMinusZeroOrNaN()) &&
1772 (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() ||
1773 NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Signed32()))) {
1774 // => signed Int32Mod
1775 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
1776 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Mod(node));
1777 return;
1778 }
1779
1780 // Try to use type feedback.
1781 NumberOperationHint hint = NumberOperationHintOf(node->op());
1782
1783 // Handle the case when no uint32 checks on inputs are necessary
1784 // (but an overflow check is needed on the output).
1785 if (BothInputsAreUnsigned32(node)) {
1786 if (hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
1787 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
1788 MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Unsigned32());
1789 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToUint32OverflowOp(node);
1790 return;
1791 }
1792 }
1793
1794 // Handle the case when no int32 checks on inputs are necessary
1795 // (but an overflow check is needed on the output).
1796 if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::Signed32())) {
1797 // If both the inputs the feedback are int32, use the overflow op.
1798 if (hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
1799 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
1800 MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Signed32());
1801 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToInt32OverflowOp(node);
1802 return;
1803 }
1804 }
1805
1806 if (hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
1807 // If the result is truncated, we only need to check the inputs.
1808 // For the left hand side we just propagate the identify zeros
1809 // mode of the {truncation}; and for modulus the sign of the
1810 // right hand side doesn't matter anyways, so in particular there's
1811 // no observable difference between a 0 and a -0 then.
1812 UseInfo const lhs_use =
1813 CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, truncation.identify_zeros());
1814 UseInfo const rhs_use =
1815 CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros);
1816 if (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
1817 VisitBinop<T>(node, lhs_use, rhs_use, MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1818 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Mod(node));
1819 } else if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZeroOrNaN())) {
1820 Type const restriction =
1821 truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero() &&
1822 TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Maybe(Type::MinusZero())
1823 ? Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero()
1824 : Type::Unsigned32();
1825 VisitBinop<T>(node, lhs_use, rhs_use, MachineRepresentation::kWord32,
1826 restriction);
1827 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToUint32OverflowOp(node);
1828 } else {
1829 Type const restriction =
1830 truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero() &&
1831 TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Maybe(Type::MinusZero())
1832 ? Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()
1833 : Type::Signed32();
1834 VisitBinop<T>(node, lhs_use, rhs_use, MachineRepresentation::kWord32,
1835 restriction);
1836 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToInt32OverflowOp(node);
1837 }
1838 return;
1839 }
1840
1841 if (TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) &&
1842 TypeOf(node->InputAt(1)).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) &&
1843 (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() ||
1844 NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()))) {
1845 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
1846 MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Number());
1847 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Uint32Mod(node));
1848 return;
1849 }
1850 if (TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Signed32()) &&
1851 TypeOf(node->InputAt(1)).Is(Type::Signed32()) &&
1852 (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() ||
1853 NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Signed32()))) {
1854 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
1855 MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Number());
1856 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Mod(node));
1857 return;
1858 }
1859
1860 // default case => Float64Mod
1861 // For the left hand side we just propagate the identify zeros
1862 // mode of the {truncation}; and for modulus the sign of the
1863 // right hand side doesn't matter anyways, so in particular there's
1864 // no observable difference between a 0 and a -0 then.
1865 UseInfo const lhs_use = UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64(
1866 truncation.identify_zeros(), FeedbackSource());
1867 UseInfo const rhs_use = UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64(
1868 kIdentifyZeros, FeedbackSource());
1869 VisitBinop<T>(node, lhs_use, rhs_use, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64,
1870 Type::Number());
1871 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
1872 }
1873
1874 // Just assert for Propagate and Retype. Lower specialized below.
1875 template <Phase T>
1876 void InsertUnreachableIfNecessary(Node* node) {
1877 static_assert(propagate<T>() || retype<T>(),
1878 "This version of InsertUnreachableIfNecessary has to be "
1879 "called in the Propagate or Retype phase.");
1880 }
1881
1882 template <Phase T>
1883 void VisitCheckBounds(Node* node, SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
1884 CheckBoundsParameters const& p = CheckBoundsParametersOf(node->op());
1885 FeedbackSource const& feedback = p.check_parameters().feedback();
1886 Type const index_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
1887 Type const length_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
1888
1889 // Conversions, if requested and needed, will be handled by the
1890 // representation changer, not by the lower-level Checked*Bounds operators.
1891 CheckBoundsFlags new_flags =
1892 p.flags().without(CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero);
1893
1894 if (length_type.Is(Type::Unsigned31())) {
1895 if (index_type.Is(Type::Integral32()) ||
1896 (index_type.Is(Type::Integral32OrMinusZero()) &&
1897 p.flags() & CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero)) {
1898 // Map the values in the [-2^31,-1] range to the [2^31,2^32-1] range,
1899 // which will be considered out-of-bounds because the {length_type} is
1900 // limited to Unsigned31. This also converts -0 to 0.
1901 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
1902 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1903 if (lower<T>()) {
1904 if (index_type.IsNone() || length_type.IsNone() ||
1905 (index_type.Min() >= 0.0 &&
1906 index_type.Max() < length_type.Min())) {
1907 // The bounds check is redundant if we already know that
1908 // the index is within the bounds of [0.0, length[.
1909 // TODO(neis): Move this into TypedOptimization?
1910 if (v8_flags.turbo_typer_hardening) {
1911 new_flags |= CheckBoundsFlag::kAbortOnOutOfBounds;
1912 } else {
1913 DeferReplacement(node, NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0));
1914 return;
1915 }
1916 }
1917 ChangeOp(node,
1918 simplified()->CheckedUint32Bounds(feedback, new_flags));
1919 }
1920 } else if (p.flags() & CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero) {
1921 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::CheckedTaggedAsArrayIndex(feedback),
1922 UseInfo::Word(), MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
1923 if (lower<T>()) {
1924 if (jsgraph_->machine()->Is64()) {
1925 ChangeOp(node,
1926 simplified()->CheckedUint64Bounds(feedback, new_flags));
1927 } else {
1928 ChangeOp(node,
1929 simplified()->CheckedUint32Bounds(feedback, new_flags));
1930 }
1931 }
1932 } else {
1933 VisitBinop<T>(
1934 node, UseInfo::CheckedSigned32AsWord32(kDistinguishZeros, feedback),
1935 UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(), MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
1936 if (lower<T>()) {
1937 ChangeOp(node,
1938 simplified()->CheckedUint32Bounds(feedback, new_flags));
1939 }
1940 }
1941 } else {
1942 CHECK(length_type.Is(type_cache_->kPositiveSafeInteger));
1943 IdentifyZeros zero_handling =
1944 (p.flags() & CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero)
1945 ? kIdentifyZeros
1946 : kDistinguishZeros;
1947 VisitBinop<T>(node,
1948 UseInfo::CheckedSigned64AsWord64(zero_handling, feedback),
1949 UseInfo::Word64(), MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
1950 if (lower<T>()) {
1951 ChangeOp(node, simplified()->CheckedUint64Bounds(feedback, new_flags));
1952 }
1953 }
1954 }
1955
1956 UseInfo UseInfoForFastApiCallArgument(CTypeInfo type,
1957 CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation repr,
1958 FeedbackSource const& feedback) {
1959 switch (type.GetSequenceType()) {
1960 case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kScalar: {
1961 uint8_t flags = uint8_t(type.GetFlags());
1962 if (flags & uint8_t(CTypeInfo::Flags::kEnforceRangeBit) ||
1963 flags & uint8_t(CTypeInfo::Flags::kClampBit)) {
1964 DCHECK(repr != CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation::kBigInt);
1965 // If the parameter is marked as `kEnforceRange` or `kClampBit`, then
1966 // special type conversion gets added explicitly to the generated
1967 // code. Therefore it is sufficient here to only require here that the
1968 // value is a Float64, even though the C++ signature actually asks for
1969 // an `int32_t`.
1970 return UseInfo::CheckedNumberAsFloat64(kIdentifyZeros, feedback);
1971 }
1972 switch (type.GetType()) {
1973 case CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid:
1974 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint8:
1975 UNREACHABLE();
1976 case CTypeInfo::Type::kBool:
1977 return UseInfo::Bool();
1978 case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt32:
1979 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint32:
1980 return UseInfo::CheckedNumberAsWord32(feedback);
1981 // TODO(mslekova): We deopt for unsafe integers, but ultimately we
1982 // want to make this less restrictive in order to stay on the fast
1983 // path.
1984 case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt64:
1985 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint64:
1986 if (repr == CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation::kBigInt) {
1987 return UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(feedback);
1988 } else if (repr == CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation::kNumber) {
1989 return UseInfo::CheckedSigned64AsWord64(kIdentifyZeros, feedback);
1990 } else {
1991 UNREACHABLE();
1992 }
1993 case CTypeInfo::Type::kAny:
1994 return UseInfo::CheckedSigned64AsWord64(kIdentifyZeros, feedback);
1995 case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat32:
1996 case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat64:
1997 return UseInfo::CheckedNumberAsFloat64(kDistinguishZeros, feedback);
1998 case CTypeInfo::Type::kPointer:
1999 case CTypeInfo::Type::kV8Value:
2000 case CTypeInfo::Type::kSeqOneByteString:
2001 case CTypeInfo::Type::kApiObject:
2002 return UseInfo::AnyTagged();
2003 }
2004 }
2005 case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kIsSequence: {
2006 CHECK_EQ(type.GetType(), CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid);
2007 return UseInfo::AnyTagged();
2008 }
2009 START_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
2010 case CTypeInfo::SequenceType::kIsTypedArray: {
2011 return UseInfo::AnyTagged();
2012 }
2013 END_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
2014 default: {
2015 UNREACHABLE(); // TODO(mslekova): Implement array buffers.
2016 }
2017 }
2018 }
2019
2020 static constexpr int kInitialArgumentsCount = 10;
2021
2022 template <Phase T>
2023 void VisitFastApiCall(Node* node, SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
2024 FastApiCallParameters const& op_params =
2025 FastApiCallParametersOf(node->op());
2026 // We only consider the first function signature here. In case of function
2027 // overloads, we only support the case of two functions that differ for one
2028 // argument, which must be a JSArray in one function and a TypedArray in the
2029 // other function, and both JSArrays and TypedArrays have the same UseInfo
2030 // UseInfo::AnyTagged(). All the other argument types must match.
2031 const CFunctionInfo* c_signature = op_params.c_function().signature;
2032 const int c_arg_count = c_signature->ArgumentCount();
2033 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = op_params.descriptor();
2034 // Arguments for CallApiCallbackOptimizedXXX builtin (including context)
2035 // plus JS arguments (including receiver).
2036 int slow_arg_count = static_cast<int>(call_descriptor->ParameterCount());
2037 const int value_input_count = node->op()->ValueInputCount();
2038 CHECK_EQ(FastApiCallNode::ArityForArgc(c_arg_count, slow_arg_count),
2039 value_input_count);
2040
2041 FastApiCallNode n(node);
2042
2043 base::SmallVector<UseInfo, kInitialArgumentsCount> arg_use_info(
2044 c_arg_count);
2045 // Propagate representation information from TypeInfo.
2046 int cursor = 0;
2047 for (int i = 0; i < c_arg_count; i++) {
2048 arg_use_info[i] = UseInfoForFastApiCallArgument(
2049 c_signature->ArgumentInfo(i), c_signature->GetInt64Representation(),
2050 op_params.feedback());
2051 ProcessInput<T>(node, cursor++, arg_use_info[i]);
2052 }
2053 // Callback data for fast call.
2054 DCHECK_EQ(n.CallbackDataIndex(), cursor);
2055 ProcessInput<T>(node, cursor++, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
2056
2057 // The call code for the slow call.
2058 ProcessInput<T>(node, cursor++, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
2059 // For the slow builtin parameters (indexes [1, ..., params]), propagate
2060 // representation information from call descriptor.
2061 for (int i = 1; i <= slow_arg_count; i++) {
2062 ProcessInput<T>(node, cursor++,
2063 TruncatingUseInfoFromRepresentation(
2064 call_descriptor->GetInputType(i).representation()));
2065 }
2066 // Visit frame state input as tagged.
2067 DCHECK_EQ(n.FrameStateIndex(), cursor);
2068 ProcessInput<T>(node, cursor++, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
2069 DCHECK_EQ(cursor, value_input_count);
2070
2071 // Effect and Control.
2072 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, value_input_count);
2073
2074 CTypeInfo return_type = op_params.c_function().signature->ReturnInfo();
2075 switch (return_type.GetType()) {
2076 case CTypeInfo::Type::kBool:
2077 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2078 return;
2079 case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat32:
2080 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kFloat32);
2081 return;
2082 case CTypeInfo::Type::kFloat64:
2083 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
2084 return;
2085 case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt32:
2086 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2087 return;
2088 case CTypeInfo::Type::kInt64:
2089 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint64:
2090 if (c_signature->GetInt64Representation() ==
2091 CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation::kBigInt) {
2092 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
2093 return;
2094 }
2095 DCHECK_EQ(c_signature->GetInt64Representation(),
2096 CFunctionInfo::Int64Representation::kNumber);
2097 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
2098 return;
2099 case CTypeInfo::Type::kSeqOneByteString:
2100 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
2101 return;
2102 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint32:
2103 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2104 return;
2105 case CTypeInfo::Type::kUint8:
2106 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord8);
2107 return;
2108 case CTypeInfo::Type::kAny:
2109 // This type is only supposed to be used for parameters, not returns.
2110 UNREACHABLE();
2111 case CTypeInfo::Type::kPointer:
2112 case CTypeInfo::Type::kApiObject:
2113 case CTypeInfo::Type::kV8Value:
2114 case CTypeInfo::Type::kVoid:
2115 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
2116 return;
2117 }
2118 }
2119
2120 template <Phase T>
2121 bool TryOptimizeBigInt64Shift(Node* node, const Truncation& truncation,
2122 SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
2123 DCHECK(Is64());
2124 if (!truncation.IsUsedAsWord64()) return false;
2125
2126 Type input_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0));
2127 Type shift_amount_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
2128
2129 if (!shift_amount_type.IsHeapConstant()) return false;
2130 HeapObjectRef ref = shift_amount_type.AsHeapConstant()->Ref();
2131 if (!ref.IsBigInt()) return false;
2132 BigIntRef bigint = ref.AsBigInt();
2133 bool lossless = false;
2134 int64_t shift_amount = bigint.AsInt64(&lossless);
2135 // We bail out if we cannot represent the shift amount correctly.
2136 if (!lossless) return false;
2137
2138 // Canonicalize {shift_amount}.
2139 bool is_shift_left =
2140 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntShiftLeft;
2141 if (shift_amount < 0) {
2142 // A shift amount of abs(std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()) is not
2143 // representable.
2144 if (shift_amount == std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min()) return false;
2145 is_shift_left = !is_shift_left;
2146 shift_amount = -shift_amount;
2147 DCHECK_GT(shift_amount, 0);
2148 }
2149 DCHECK_GE(shift_amount, 0);
2150
2151 // If the operation is a *real* left shift, propagate truncation.
2152 // If it is a *real* right shift, the output representation is
2153 // word64 only if we know the input type is BigInt64.
2154 // Otherwise, fall through to using BigIntOperationHint.
2155 if (is_shift_left) {
2156 VisitBinop<T>(node,
2157 UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
2158 UseInfo::Any(), MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
2159 if (lower<T>()) {
2160 if (shift_amount > 63) {
2161 DeferReplacement(node, jsgraph_->Int64Constant(0));
2162 } else if (shift_amount == 0) {
2163 DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
2164 } else {
2165 DCHECK_GE(shift_amount, 1);
2166 DCHECK_LE(shift_amount, 63);
2167 ReplaceWithPureNode(
2168 node, graph()->NewNode(lowering->machine()->Word64Shl(),
2169 node->InputAt(0),
2170 jsgraph_->Int64Constant(shift_amount)));
2171 }
2172 }
2173 return true;
2174 } else if (input_type.Is(Type::SignedBigInt64())) {
2175 VisitBinop<T>(node,
2176 UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
2177 UseInfo::Any(), MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
2178 if (lower<T>()) {
2179 if (shift_amount > 63) {
2180 ReplaceWithPureNode(
2181 node,
2182 graph()->NewNode(lowering->machine()->Word64Sar(),
2183 node->InputAt(0), jsgraph_->Int64Constant(63)));
2184 } else if (shift_amount == 0) {
2185 DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
2186 } else {
2187 DCHECK_GE(shift_amount, 1);
2188 DCHECK_LE(shift_amount, 63);
2189 ReplaceWithPureNode(
2190 node, graph()->NewNode(lowering->machine()->Word64Sar(),
2191 node->InputAt(0),
2192 jsgraph_->Int64Constant(shift_amount)));
2193 }
2194 }
2195 return true;
2196 } else if (input_type.Is(Type::UnsignedBigInt64())) {
2197 VisitBinop<T>(node,
2198 UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
2199 UseInfo::Any(), MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
2200 if (lower<T>()) {
2201 if (shift_amount > 63) {
2202 DeferReplacement(node, jsgraph_->Int64Constant(0));
2203 } else if (shift_amount == 0) {
2204 DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
2205 } else {
2206 DCHECK_GE(shift_amount, 1);
2207 DCHECK_LE(shift_amount, 63);
2208 ReplaceWithPureNode(
2209 node, graph()->NewNode(lowering->machine()->Word64Shr(),
2210 node->InputAt(0),
2211 jsgraph_->Int64Constant(shift_amount)));
2212 }
2213 }
2214 return true;
2215 }
2216
2217 // None of the cases we can optimize here.
2218 return false;
2219 }
2220
2221#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2222 static MachineType MachineTypeForWasmReturnType(
2223 wasm::CanonicalValueType type) {
2224 switch (type.kind()) {
2225 case wasm::kI32:
2226 return MachineType::Int32();
2227 case wasm::kI64:
2228 return MachineType::Int64();
2229 case wasm::kF32:
2230 return MachineType::Float32();
2231 case wasm::kF64:
2232 return MachineType::Float64();
2233 case wasm::kRef:
2234 case wasm::kRefNull:
2235 return MachineType::AnyTagged();
2236 default:
2237 UNREACHABLE();
2238 }
2239 }
2240
2241 UseInfo UseInfoForJSWasmCallArgument(Node* input,
2242 wasm::CanonicalValueType type,
2243 FeedbackSource const& feedback) {
2244 // If the input type is a Number or Oddball, we can directly convert the
2245 // input into the Wasm native type of the argument. If not, we return
2246 // UseInfo::AnyTagged to signal that WasmWrapperGraphBuilder will need to
2247 // add Nodes to perform the conversion (in WasmWrapperGraphBuilder::FromJS).
2248 switch (type.kind()) {
2249 case wasm::kI32:
2250 return UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsWord32(feedback);
2251 case wasm::kI64:
2252 return UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(feedback);
2253 case wasm::kF32:
2254 case wasm::kF64:
2255 // For Float32, TruncateFloat64ToFloat32 will be inserted later in
2256 // WasmWrapperGraphBuilder::BuildJSToWasmWrapper.
2257 return UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64(kDistinguishZeros,
2258 feedback);
2259 case wasm::kRef:
2260 case wasm::kRefNull:
2261 return UseInfo::AnyTagged();
2262 default:
2263 UNREACHABLE();
2264 }
2265 }
2266
2267 template <Phase T>
2268 void VisitJSWasmCall(Node* node, SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
2269 DCHECK_EQ(JSWasmCallNode::TargetIndex(), 0);
2270 DCHECK_EQ(JSWasmCallNode::ReceiverIndex(), 1);
2271 DCHECK_EQ(JSWasmCallNode::FirstArgumentIndex(), 2);
2272
2273 JSWasmCallNode n(node);
2274
2275 JSWasmCallParameters const& params = n.Parameters();
2276 const wasm::CanonicalSig* wasm_signature = params.signature();
2277 int wasm_arg_count = static_cast<int>(wasm_signature->parameter_count());
2278 DCHECK_EQ(wasm_arg_count, n.ArgumentCount());
2279
2280 base::SmallVector<UseInfo, kInitialArgumentsCount> arg_use_info(
2281 wasm_arg_count);
2282
2283 // Visit JSFunction and Receiver nodes.
2284 ProcessInput<T>(node, JSWasmCallNode::TargetIndex(), UseInfo::Any());
2285 ProcessInput<T>(node, JSWasmCallNode::ReceiverIndex(), UseInfo::Any());
2286
2287 // Propagate representation information from TypeInfo.
2288 for (int i = 0; i < wasm_arg_count; i++) {
2289 TNode<Object> input = n.Argument(i);
2290 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(input);
2291 arg_use_info[i] = UseInfoForJSWasmCallArgument(
2292 input, wasm_signature->GetParam(i), params.feedback());
2293 ProcessInput<T>(node, JSWasmCallNode::ArgumentIndex(i), arg_use_info[i]);
2294 }
2295
2296 // Visit value, context and frame state inputs as tagged.
2297 int first_effect_index = NodeProperties::FirstEffectIndex(node);
2298 DCHECK(first_effect_index >
2299 JSWasmCallNode::FirstArgumentIndex() + wasm_arg_count);
2300 for (int i = JSWasmCallNode::FirstArgumentIndex() + wasm_arg_count;
2301 i < first_effect_index; i++) {
2302 ProcessInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
2303 }
2304
2305 // Effect and Control.
2306 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, NodeProperties::FirstEffectIndex(node));
2307
2308 if (wasm_signature->return_count() == 1) {
2309 MachineType return_type =
2310 MachineTypeForWasmReturnType(wasm_signature->GetReturn());
2311 SetOutput<T>(
2312 node, return_type.representation(),
2313 JSWasmCallNode::TypeForWasmReturnType(wasm_signature->GetReturn()));
2314 } else {
2315 DCHECK_EQ(wasm_signature->return_count(), 0);
2316 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
2317 }
2318
2319 // The actual lowering of JSWasmCall nodes happens later, in the subsequent
2320 // "wasm-inlining" phase.
2321 }
2322#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
2323
2324 // Dispatching routine for visiting the node {node} with the usage {use}.
2325 // Depending on the operator, propagate new usage info to the inputs.
2326 template <Phase T>
2327 void VisitNode(Node* node, Truncation truncation,
2328 SimplifiedLowering* lowering) {
2329 tick_counter_->TickAndMaybeEnterSafepoint();
2330
2331 if (lower<T>()) {
2332 // Kill non-effectful operations that have a None-type input and are thus
2333 // dead code. Otherwise we might end up lowering the operation in a way,
2334 // e.g. by replacing it with a constant, that cuts the dependency on a
2335 // deopting operation (the producer of the None type), possibly resulting
2336 // in a nonsense schedule.
2337 if (node->op()->EffectOutputCount() == 0 &&
2338 node->op()->ControlOutputCount() == 0 &&
2339 node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kDeadValue &&
2340 node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kStateValues &&
2341 node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kFrameState &&
2342 node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kPhi) {
2343 for (int i = 0; i < node->op()->ValueInputCount(); i++) {
2344 Node* input = node->InputAt(i);
2345 if (TypeOf(input).IsNone()) {
2346 node->ReplaceInput(0, input);
2347 node->TrimInputCount(1);
2348 ChangeOp(node,
2349 common()->DeadValue(GetInfo(node)->representation()));
2350 return;
2351 }
2352 }
2353 } else {
2354 InsertUnreachableIfNecessary<T>(node);
2355 }
2356 }
2357
2358 // Unconditionally eliminate unused pure nodes (only relevant if there's
2359 // a pure operation in between two effectful ones, where the last one
2360 // is unused).
2361 // Note: We must not do this for constants, as they are cached and we
2362 // would thus kill the cached {node} during lowering (i.e. replace all
2363 // uses with Dead), but at that point some node lowering might have
2364 // already taken the constant {node} from the cache (while it was not
2365 // yet killed) and we would afterwards replace that use with Dead as well.
2366 if (node->op()->ValueInputCount() > 0 &&
2367 node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kPure) && truncation.IsUnused()) {
2368 return VisitUnused<T>(node);
2369 }
2370
2371 switch (node->opcode()) {
2372 //------------------------------------------------------------------
2373 // Common operators.
2374 //------------------------------------------------------------------
2375 case IrOpcode::kStart:
2376 // We use Start as a terminator for the frame state chain, so even
2377 // tho Start doesn't really produce a value, we have to say Tagged
2378 // here, otherwise the input conversion will fail.
2379 return VisitLeaf<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
2380 case IrOpcode::kParameter:
2381 return VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::None(),
2382 linkage()
2383 ->GetParameterType(ParameterIndexOf(node->op()))
2384 .representation());
2385 case IrOpcode::kInt32Constant:
2386 DCHECK_EQ(0, node->InputCount());
2387 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2388 DCHECK(NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Machine()));
2389 if (V8_UNLIKELY(verification_enabled())) {
2390 // During lowering, SimplifiedLowering generates Int32Constants which
2391 // need to be treated differently by the verifier than the
2392 // Int32Constants introduced explicitly in machine graphs. To be able
2393 // to distinguish them, we record those that are being visited here
2394 // because they were generated before SimplifiedLowering.
2395 if (propagate<T>()) {
2396 verifier_->RecordMachineUsesOfConstant(node, node->uses());
2397 }
2398 }
2399 return;
2400 case IrOpcode::kInt64Constant:
2401 return VisitLeaf<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
2402 case IrOpcode::kExternalConstant:
2403 return VisitLeaf<T>(node, MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
2404 case IrOpcode::kNumberConstant: {
2405 double const value = OpParameter<double>(node->op());
2406 int value_as_int;
2407 if (DoubleToSmiInteger(value, &value_as_int)) {
2408 VisitLeaf<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned);
2409 if (lower<T>()) {
2410 intptr_t smi = base::bit_cast<intptr_t>(Smi::FromInt(value_as_int));
2411 Node* constant = InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
2412 NodeProperties::GetType(node),
2413 lowering->jsgraph()->IntPtrConstant(smi));
2414 DeferReplacement(node, constant);
2415 }
2416 return;
2417 }
2418 VisitLeaf<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
2419 return;
2420 }
2421 case IrOpcode::kHeapConstant:
2422 return VisitLeaf<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
2423 case IrOpcode::kTrustedHeapConstant:
2424 return VisitLeaf<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
2425 case IrOpcode::kPointerConstant: {
2426 VisitLeaf<T>(node, MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
2427 if (lower<T>()) {
2428 intptr_t const value = OpParameter<intptr_t>(node->op());
2429 DeferReplacement(node, lowering->jsgraph()->IntPtrConstant(value));
2430 }
2431 return;
2432 }
2433
2434 case IrOpcode::kBranch: {
2435 const auto& p = BranchParametersOf(node->op());
2436 if (p.semantics() == BranchSemantics::kMachine) {
2437 // If this is a machine branch, the condition is a machine operator,
2438 // so we enter machine branch here.
2439 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Any());
2440 } else {
2441 DCHECK(TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Boolean()));
2442 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Bool());
2443 if (lower<T>()) {
2444 ChangeOp(node,
2445 common()->Branch(p.hint(), BranchSemantics::kMachine));
2446 }
2447 }
2448 EnqueueInput<T>(node, NodeProperties::FirstControlIndex(node));
2449 return;
2450 }
2451 case IrOpcode::kSwitch:
2452 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32());
2453 EnqueueInput<T>(node, NodeProperties::FirstControlIndex(node));
2454 return;
2455 case IrOpcode::kSelect: {
2456 const auto& p = SelectParametersOf(node->op());
2457 if (p.semantics() == BranchSemantics::kMachine) {
2458 // If this is a machine select, all inputs are machine operators.
2459 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Any());
2460 ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::Any());
2461 ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::Any());
2462 SetOutput<T>(node, p.representation());
2463 } else {
2464 VisitSelect<T>(node, truncation, lowering);
2465 }
2466 return;
2467 }
2468 case IrOpcode::kPhi:
2469 return VisitPhi<T>(node, truncation, lowering);
2470 case IrOpcode::kCall:
2471 return VisitCall<T>(node, lowering);
2472 case IrOpcode::kAssert: {
2473 const auto& p = AssertParametersOf(node->op());
2474 if (p.semantics() == BranchSemantics::kMachine) {
2475 // If this is a machine condition already, we don't need to do
2476 // anything.
2477 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Any());
2478 } else {
2479 DCHECK(TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Boolean()));
2480 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Bool());
2481 if (lower<T>()) {
2482 ChangeOp(node, common()->Assert(BranchSemantics::kMachine,
2483 p.condition_string(), p.file(),
2484 p.line()));
2485 }
2486 }
2487 EnqueueInput<T>(node, NodeProperties::FirstControlIndex(node));
2488 return;
2489 }
2490
2491 //------------------------------------------------------------------
2492 // JavaScript operators.
2493 //------------------------------------------------------------------
2494 case IrOpcode::kJSToNumber:
2495 case IrOpcode::kJSToNumberConvertBigInt:
2496 case IrOpcode::kJSToNumeric: {
2497 DCHECK(NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Union(
2498 Type::BigInt(), Type::NumberOrOddball(), graph()->zone())));
2499 VisitInputs<T>(node);
2500 // TODO(bmeurer): Optimize somewhat based on input type?
2501 if (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
2502 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2503 if (lower<T>())
2504 lowering->DoJSToNumberOrNumericTruncatesToWord32(node, this);
2505 } else if (truncation.TruncatesOddballAndBigIntToNumber()) {
2506 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
2507 if (lower<T>())
2508 lowering->DoJSToNumberOrNumericTruncatesToFloat64(node, this);
2509 } else {
2510 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
2511 }
2512 return;
2513 }
2514 case IrOpcode::kJSToBigInt:
2515 case IrOpcode::kJSToBigIntConvertNumber: {
2516 VisitInputs<T>(node);
2517 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
2518 return;
2519 }
2520
2521 //------------------------------------------------------------------
2522 // Simplified operators.
2523 //------------------------------------------------------------------
2524 case IrOpcode::kToBoolean: {
2525 if (truncation.IsUsedAsBool()) {
2526 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Bool());
2527 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2528 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
2529 } else {
2530 VisitInputs<T>(node);
2531 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
2532 }
2533 return;
2534 }
2535 case IrOpcode::kBooleanNot: {
2536 if (lower<T>()) {
2537 NodeInfo* input_info = GetInfo(node->InputAt(0));
2538 if (input_info->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kBit) {
2539 // BooleanNot(x: kRepBit) => Word32Equal(x, #0)
2540 node->AppendInput(jsgraph_->zone(), jsgraph_->Int32Constant(0));
2541 ChangeOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Equal());
2542 } else if (CanBeTaggedPointer(input_info->representation())) {
2543 // BooleanNot(x: kRepTagged) => TaggedEqual(x, #false)
2544 node->AppendInput(jsgraph_->zone(), jsgraph_->FalseConstant());
2545 ChangeOp(node, lowering->machine()->TaggedEqual());
2546 } else {
2547 DCHECK(TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).IsNone());
2548 DeferReplacement(node, lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0));
2549 }
2550 } else {
2551 // No input representation requirement; adapt during lowering.
2552 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTruncatingToBool());
2553 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2554 }
2555 return;
2556 }
2557 case IrOpcode::kNumberEqual: {
2558 Type const lhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
2559 Type const rhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
2560 // Regular number comparisons in JavaScript generally identify zeros,
2561 // so we always pass kIdentifyZeros for the inputs, and in addition
2562 // we can truncate -0 to 0 for otherwise Unsigned32 or Signed32 inputs.
2563 // For equality we also handle the case that one side is non-zero, in
2564 // which case we allow to truncate NaN to 0 on the other side.
2565 if ((lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero()) &&
2566 rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero())) ||
2567 (lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZeroOrNaN()) &&
2568 rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZeroOrNaN()) &&
2569 OneInputCannotBe(node, type_cache_->kZeroish))) {
2570 // => unsigned Int32Cmp
2571 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2572 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2573 if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Uint32Op(node));
2574 return;
2575 }
2576 if ((lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) &&
2577 rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero())) ||
2578 (lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZeroOrNaN()) &&
2579 rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZeroOrNaN()) &&
2580 OneInputCannotBe(node, type_cache_->kZeroish))) {
2581 // => signed Int32Cmp
2582 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2583 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2584 if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2585 return;
2586 }
2587 if (lhs_type.Is(Type::Boolean()) && rhs_type.Is(Type::Boolean())) {
2588 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::Bool(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2589 if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Equal());
2590 return;
2591 }
2592 // => Float64Cmp
2593 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(kIdentifyZeros),
2594 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2595 if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
2596 return;
2597 }
2598 case IrOpcode::kNumberLessThan:
2599 case IrOpcode::kNumberLessThanOrEqual: {
2600 Type const lhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
2601 Type const rhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
2602 // Regular number comparisons in JavaScript generally identify zeros,
2603 // so we always pass kIdentifyZeros for the inputs, and in addition
2604 // we can truncate -0 to 0 for otherwise Unsigned32 or Signed32 inputs.
2605 if (lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero()) &&
2606 rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero())) {
2607 // => unsigned Int32Cmp
2608 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2609 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2610 if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Uint32Op(node));
2611 } else if (lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) &&
2612 rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero())) {
2613 // => signed Int32Cmp
2614 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2615 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2616 if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2617 } else {
2618 // => Float64Cmp
2619 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(kIdentifyZeros),
2620 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2621 if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
2622 }
2623 return;
2624 }
2625
2626 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeSafeIntegerAdd:
2627 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeSafeIntegerSubtract:
2628 return VisitSpeculativeIntegerAdditiveOp<T>(node, truncation, lowering);
2629
2630 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberAdd:
2631 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberSubtract:
2632 return VisitSpeculativeAdditiveOp<T>(node, truncation, lowering);
2633
2634 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberLessThan:
2635 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberLessThanOrEqual:
2636 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberEqual: {
2637 Type const lhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
2638 Type const rhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
2639 // Regular number comparisons in JavaScript generally identify zeros,
2640 // so we always pass kIdentifyZeros for the inputs, and in addition
2641 // we can truncate -0 to 0 for otherwise Unsigned32 or Signed32 inputs.
2642 if (lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero()) &&
2643 rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero())) {
2644 // => unsigned Int32Cmp
2645 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2646 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2647 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Uint32Op(node));
2648 return;
2649 } else if (lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) &&
2650 rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero())) {
2651 // => signed Int32Cmp
2652 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2653 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2654 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2655 return;
2656 } else if (lhs_type.Is(Type::Boolean()) &&
2657 rhs_type.Is(Type::Boolean())) {
2658 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::Bool(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2659 if (lower<T>())
2660 ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Equal());
2661 return;
2662 }
2663 // Try to use type feedback.
2664 NumberOperationHint hint = NumberOperationHintOf(node->op());
2665 switch (hint) {
2666 case NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall:
2667 if (propagate<T>()) {
2668 VisitBinop<T>(
2669 node, CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros),
2670 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2671 } else if (retype<T>()) {
2672 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kBit, Type::Any());
2673 } else {
2674 DCHECK(lower<T>());
2675 Node* lhs = node->InputAt(0);
2676 Node* rhs = node->InputAt(1);
2677 if (IsNodeRepresentationTagged(lhs) &&
2678 IsNodeRepresentationTagged(rhs)) {
2679 VisitBinop<T>(node,
2680 UseInfo::CheckedSignedSmallAsTaggedSigned(
2681 FeedbackSource(), kIdentifyZeros),
2682 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2683 ChangeToPureOp(
2684 node, changer_->TaggedSignedOperatorFor(node->opcode()));
2685
2686 } else {
2687 VisitBinop<T>(
2688 node, CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros),
2689 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2690 ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2691 }
2692 }
2693 return;
2694 case NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs:
2695 // This doesn't make sense for compare operations.
2696 UNREACHABLE();
2697 case NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball:
2698 // Abstract and strict equality don't perform ToNumber conversions
2699 // on Oddballs, so make sure we don't accidentially sneak in a
2700 // hint with Oddball feedback here.
2701 DCHECK_NE(IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberEqual, node->opcode());
2702 [[fallthrough]];
2703 case NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrBoolean:
2704 case NumberOperationHint::kNumber:
2705 VisitBinop<T>(node,
2706 CheckedUseInfoAsFloat64FromHint(
2707 hint, FeedbackSource(), kIdentifyZeros),
2708 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
2709 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
2710 return;
2711 }
2712 UNREACHABLE();
2713 return;
2714 }
2715
2716 case IrOpcode::kNumberAdd:
2717 case IrOpcode::kNumberSubtract: {
2718 if (TypeOf(node->InputAt(0))
2719 .Is(type_cache_->kAdditiveSafeIntegerOrMinusZero) &&
2720 TypeOf(node->InputAt(1))
2721 .Is(type_cache_->kAdditiveSafeIntegerOrMinusZero) &&
2722 (TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Signed32()) ||
2723 TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) ||
2724 truncation.IsUsedAsWord32())) {
2725 // => Int32Add/Sub
2726 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2727 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2728 } else if (jsgraph_->machine()->Is64() &&
2729 BothInputsAre(node, type_cache_->kSafeInteger) &&
2730 GetUpperBound(node).Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger)) {
2731 // => Int64Add/Sub
2732 VisitInt64Binop<T>(node);
2733 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Int64Op(node));
2734 } else {
2735 // => Float64Add/Sub
2736 VisitFloat64Binop<T>(node);
2737 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
2738 }
2739 return;
2740 }
2741 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberMultiply: {
2742 if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::Integral32()) &&
2743 (NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Signed32()) ||
2744 NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) ||
2745 (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() &&
2746 NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(
2747 type_cache_->kSafeIntegerOrMinusZero)))) {
2748 // Multiply reduces to Int32Mul if the inputs are integers, and
2749 // (a) the output is either known to be Signed32, or
2750 // (b) the output is known to be Unsigned32, or
2751 // (c) the uses are truncating and the result is in the safe
2752 // integer range.
2753 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2754 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2755 return;
2756 }
2757 // Try to use type feedback.
2758 NumberOperationHint hint = NumberOperationHintOf(node->op());
2759 Type input0_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
2760 Type input1_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
2761
2762 // Handle the case when no int32 checks on inputs are necessary
2763 // (but an overflow check is needed on the output).
2764 if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::Signed32())) {
2765 // If both inputs and feedback are int32, use the overflow op.
2766 if (hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
2767 VisitForCheckedInt32Mul<T>(node, truncation, input0_type,
2768 input1_type,
2769 UseInfo::TruncatingWord32());
2770 return;
2771 }
2772 }
2773
2774 if (hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
2775 VisitForCheckedInt32Mul<T>(node, truncation, input0_type, input1_type,
2776 CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint));
2777 return;
2778 }
2779
2780 // Checked float64 x float64 => float64
2781 VisitBinop<T>(node,
2782 UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64(
2783 kDistinguishZeros, FeedbackSource()),
2784 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, Type::Number());
2785 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
2786 return;
2787 }
2788 case IrOpcode::kNumberMultiply: {
2789 if (TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Integral32()) &&
2790 TypeOf(node->InputAt(1)).Is(Type::Integral32()) &&
2791 (TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Signed32()) ||
2792 TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) ||
2793 (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() &&
2794 TypeOf(node).Is(type_cache_->kSafeIntegerOrMinusZero)))) {
2795 // Multiply reduces to Int32Mul if the inputs are integers, and
2796 // (a) the output is either known to be Signed32, or
2797 // (b) the output is known to be Unsigned32, or
2798 // (c) the uses are truncating and the result is in the safe
2799 // integer range.
2800 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2801 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2802 return;
2803 }
2804 // Number x Number => Float64Mul
2805 VisitFloat64Binop<T>(node);
2806 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
2807 return;
2808 }
2809 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberDivide: {
2810 if (BothInputsAreUnsigned32(node) && truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
2811 // => unsigned Uint32Div
2812 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2813 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Uint32Div(node));
2814 return;
2815 }
2816 if (BothInputsAreSigned32(node)) {
2817 if (NodeProperties::GetType(node).Is(Type::Signed32())) {
2818 // => signed Int32Div
2819 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2820 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Div(node));
2821 return;
2822 }
2823 if (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
2824 // => signed Int32Div
2825 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2826 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Div(node));
2827 return;
2828 }
2829 }
2830
2831 // Try to use type feedback.
2832 NumberOperationHint hint = NumberOperationHintOf(node->op());
2833
2834 // Handle the case when no uint32 checks on inputs are necessary
2835 // (but an overflow check is needed on the output).
2836 if (BothInputsAreUnsigned32(node)) {
2837 if (hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
2838 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2839 MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Unsigned32());
2840 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToUint32OverflowOp(node);
2841 return;
2842 }
2843 }
2844
2845 // Handle the case when no int32 checks on inputs are necessary
2846 // (but an overflow check is needed on the output).
2847 if (BothInputsAreSigned32(node)) {
2848 // If both the inputs the feedback are int32, use the overflow op.
2849 if (hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall) {
2850 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2851 MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Signed32());
2852 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToInt32OverflowOp(node);
2853 return;
2854 }
2855 }
2856
2857 if (hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall ||
2858 hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs) {
2859 // If the result is truncated, we only need to check the inputs.
2860 if (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
2861 VisitBinop<T>(node, CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint),
2862 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2863 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Div(node));
2864 return;
2865 } else if (hint != NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs) {
2866 VisitBinop<T>(node, CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint),
2867 MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Signed32());
2868 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToInt32OverflowOp(node);
2869 return;
2870 }
2871 }
2872
2873 // default case => Float64Div
2874 VisitBinop<T>(node,
2875 UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64(
2876 kDistinguishZeros, FeedbackSource()),
2877 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, Type::Number());
2878 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
2879 return;
2880 }
2881 case IrOpcode::kNumberDivide: {
2882 if (TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) &&
2883 TypeOf(node->InputAt(1)).Is(Type::Unsigned32()) &&
2884 (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() ||
2885 TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()))) {
2886 // => unsigned Uint32Div
2887 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2888 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Uint32Div(node));
2889 return;
2890 }
2891 if (TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Signed32()) &&
2892 TypeOf(node->InputAt(1)).Is(Type::Signed32()) &&
2893 (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() ||
2894 TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Signed32()))) {
2895 // => signed Int32Div
2896 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2897 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Div(node));
2898 return;
2899 }
2900 // Number x Number => Float64Div
2901 VisitFloat64Binop<T>(node);
2902 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
2903 return;
2904 }
2905 case IrOpcode::kUnsigned32Divide: {
2906 CHECK(TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Unsigned32()));
2907 CHECK(TypeOf(node->InputAt(1)).Is(Type::Unsigned32()));
2908 // => unsigned Uint32Div
2909 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2910 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Uint32Div(node));
2911 return;
2912 }
2913 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberModulus:
2914 return VisitSpeculativeNumberModulus<T>(node, truncation, lowering);
2915 case IrOpcode::kNumberModulus: {
2916 Type const lhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
2917 Type const rhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
2918 if ((lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZeroOrNaN()) &&
2919 rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZeroOrNaN())) &&
2920 (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() ||
2921 TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Unsigned32()))) {
2922 // => unsigned Uint32Mod
2923 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2924 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Uint32Mod(node));
2925 return;
2926 }
2927 if ((lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZeroOrNaN()) &&
2928 rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZeroOrNaN())) &&
2929 (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32() || TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Signed32()) ||
2930 (truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero() &&
2931 TypeOf(node).Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero())))) {
2932 // => signed Int32Mod
2933 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2934 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Int32Mod(node));
2935 return;
2936 }
2937 // => Float64Mod
2938 // For the left hand side we just propagate the identify zeros
2939 // mode of the {truncation}; and for modulus the sign of the
2940 // right hand side doesn't matter anyways, so in particular there's
2941 // no observable difference between a 0 and a -0 then.
2942 UseInfo const lhs_use =
2943 UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(truncation.identify_zeros());
2944 UseInfo const rhs_use = UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(kIdentifyZeros);
2945 VisitBinop<T>(node, lhs_use, rhs_use, MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
2946 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
2947 return;
2948 }
2949 case IrOpcode::kNumberBitwiseOr:
2950 case IrOpcode::kNumberBitwiseXor:
2951 case IrOpcode::kNumberBitwiseAnd: {
2952 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
2953 if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2954 return;
2955 }
2956 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberBitwiseOr:
2957 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberBitwiseXor:
2958 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberBitwiseAnd:
2959 VisitSpeculativeInt32Binop<T>(node);
2960 if (lower<T>()) {
2961 ChangeToPureOp(node, Int32Op(node));
2962 }
2963 return;
2964 case IrOpcode::kNumberShiftLeft: {
2965 Type rhs_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
2966 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2967 UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2968 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2969 if (lower<T>()) {
2970 MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);
2971 ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Shl());
2972 }
2973 return;
2974 }
2975 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberShiftLeft: {
2976 if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::NumberOrOddball())) {
2977 Type rhs_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
2978 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2979 UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
2980 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
2981 if (lower<T>()) {
2982 MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);
2983 ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Shl());
2984 }
2985 return;
2986 }
2987 NumberOperationHint hint = NumberOperationHintOf(node->op());
2988 Type rhs_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
2989 VisitBinop<T>(node,
2990 CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros),
2991 MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Signed32());
2992 if (lower<T>()) {
2993 MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);
2994 ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Shl());
2995 }
2996 return;
2997 }
2998 case IrOpcode::kNumberShiftRight: {
2999 Type rhs_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
3000 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3001 UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3002 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3003 if (lower<T>()) {
3004 MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);
3005 ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Sar());
3006 }
3007 return;
3008 }
3009 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberShiftRight: {
3010 if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::NumberOrOddball())) {
3011 Type rhs_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
3012 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3013 UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3014 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3015 if (lower<T>()) {
3016 MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);
3017 ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Sar());
3018 }
3019 return;
3020 }
3021 NumberOperationHint hint = NumberOperationHintOf(node->op());
3022 Type rhs_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
3023 VisitBinop<T>(node,
3024 CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros),
3025 MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Signed32());
3026 if (lower<T>()) {
3027 MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);
3028 ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Sar());
3029 }
3030 return;
3031 }
3032 case IrOpcode::kNumberShiftRightLogical: {
3033 Type rhs_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
3034 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3035 UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3036 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3037 if (lower<T>()) {
3038 MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);
3039 ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Shr());
3040 }
3041 return;
3042 }
3043 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberShiftRightLogical: {
3044 NumberOperationHint hint = NumberOperationHintOf(node->op());
3045 Type rhs_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(1));
3046 if (rhs_type.Is(type_cache_->kZeroish) &&
3047 hint == NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall &&
3048 !truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
3049 // The SignedSmall or Signed32 feedback means that the results that we
3050 // have seen so far were of type Unsigned31. We speculate that this
3051 // will continue to hold. Moreover, since the RHS is 0, the result
3052 // will just be the (converted) LHS.
3053 VisitBinop<T>(node,
3054 CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros),
3055 MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Unsigned31());
3056 if (lower<T>()) {
3057 node->RemoveInput(1);
3058 ChangeOp(node,
3059 simplified()->CheckedUint32ToInt32(FeedbackSource()));
3060 }
3061 return;
3062 }
3063 if (BothInputsAre(node, Type::NumberOrOddball())) {
3064 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3065 UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3066 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3067 if (lower<T>()) {
3068 MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);
3069 ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Shr());
3070 }
3071 return;
3072 }
3073 VisitBinop<T>(node,
3074 CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(hint, kIdentifyZeros),
3075 MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Unsigned32());
3076 if (lower<T>()) {
3077 MaskShiftOperand(node, rhs_type);
3078 ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word32Shr());
3079 }
3080 return;
3081 }
3082 case IrOpcode::kNumberAbs: {
3083 // NumberAbs maps both 0 and -0 to 0, so we can generally
3084 // pass the kIdentifyZeros truncation to its input, and
3085 // choose to ignore minus zero in all cases.
3086 Type const input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
3087 if (input_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero())) {
3088 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3089 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3090 if (lower<T>()) {
3091 DeferReplacement(
3092 node,
3093 InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
3094 Type::Intersect(input_type, Type::Unsigned32(), zone()),
3095 node->InputAt(0)));
3096 }
3097 } else if (input_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero())) {
3098 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3099 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3100 if (lower<T>()) {
3101 DeferReplacement(
3102 node,
3103 InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
3104 Type::Intersect(input_type, Type::Unsigned32(), zone()),
3105 lowering->Int32Abs(node)));
3106 }
3107 } else if (input_type.Is(type_cache_->kPositiveIntegerOrNaN)) {
3108 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(kIdentifyZeros),
3109 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3110 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
3111 } else {
3112 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(kIdentifyZeros),
3113 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3114 if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3115 }
3116 return;
3117 }
3118 case IrOpcode::kNumberClz32: {
3119 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3120 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3121 if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Uint32Op(node));
3122 return;
3123 }
3124 case IrOpcode::kNumberImul: {
3125 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3126 UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3127 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3128 if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Uint32Op(node));
3129 return;
3130 }
3131 case IrOpcode::kNumberFround: {
3132 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
3133 MachineRepresentation::kFloat32);
3134 if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3135 return;
3136 }
3137 case IrOpcode::kNumberMax: {
3138 // It is safe to use the feedback types for left and right hand side
3139 // here, since we can only narrow those types and thus we can only
3140 // promise a more specific truncation.
3141 // For NumberMax we generally propagate whether the truncation
3142 // identifies zeros to the inputs, and we choose to ignore minus
3143 // zero in those cases.
3144 Type const lhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
3145 Type const rhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
3146 if ((lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32()) &&
3147 rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32())) ||
3148 (lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero()) &&
3149 rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero()) &&
3150 truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero())) {
3151 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
3152 if (lower<T>()) {
3153 lowering->DoMax(node, lowering->machine()->Uint32LessThan(),
3154 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3155 }
3156 } else if ((lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32()) &&
3157 rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32())) ||
3158 (lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) &&
3159 rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) &&
3160 truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero())) {
3161 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
3162 if (lower<T>()) {
3163 lowering->DoMax(node, lowering->machine()->Int32LessThan(),
3164 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3165 }
3166 } else if (jsgraph_->machine()->Is64() &&
3167 lhs_type.Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger) &&
3168 rhs_type.Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger)) {
3169 VisitInt64Binop<T>(node);
3170 if (lower<T>()) {
3171 lowering->DoMax(node, lowering->machine()->Int64LessThan(),
3172 MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
3173 }
3174 } else {
3175 VisitBinop<T>(node,
3176 UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(truncation.identify_zeros()),
3177 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3178 if (lower<T>()) {
3179 // If the right hand side is not NaN, and the left hand side
3180 // is not NaN (or -0 if the difference between the zeros is
3181 // observed), we can do a simple floating point comparison here.
3182 if (lhs_type.Is(truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero()
3183 ? Type::OrderedNumber()
3184 : Type::PlainNumber()) &&
3185 rhs_type.Is(Type::OrderedNumber())) {
3186 lowering->DoMax(node, lowering->machine()->Float64LessThan(),
3187 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3188 } else {
3189 ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3190 }
3191 }
3192 }
3193 return;
3194 }
3195 case IrOpcode::kNumberMin: {
3196 // It is safe to use the feedback types for left and right hand side
3197 // here, since we can only narrow those types and thus we can only
3198 // promise a more specific truncation.
3199 // For NumberMin we generally propagate whether the truncation
3200 // identifies zeros to the inputs, and we choose to ignore minus
3201 // zero in those cases.
3202 Type const lhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
3203 Type const rhs_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
3204 if ((lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32()) &&
3205 rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32())) ||
3206 (lhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero()) &&
3207 rhs_type.Is(Type::Unsigned32OrMinusZero()) &&
3208 truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero())) {
3209 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
3210 if (lower<T>()) {
3211 lowering->DoMin(node, lowering->machine()->Uint32LessThan(),
3212 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3213 }
3214 } else if ((lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32()) &&
3215 rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32())) ||
3216 (lhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) &&
3217 rhs_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero()) &&
3218 truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero())) {
3219 VisitWord32TruncatingBinop<T>(node);
3220 if (lower<T>()) {
3221 lowering->DoMin(node, lowering->machine()->Int32LessThan(),
3222 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3223 }
3224 } else if (jsgraph_->machine()->Is64() &&
3225 lhs_type.Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger) &&
3226 rhs_type.Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger)) {
3227 VisitInt64Binop<T>(node);
3228 if (lower<T>()) {
3229 lowering->DoMin(node, lowering->machine()->Int64LessThan(),
3230 MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
3231 }
3232 } else {
3233 VisitBinop<T>(node,
3234 UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(truncation.identify_zeros()),
3235 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3236 if (lower<T>()) {
3237 // If the left hand side is not NaN, and the right hand side
3238 // is not NaN (or -0 if the difference between the zeros is
3239 // observed), we can do a simple floating point comparison here.
3240 if (lhs_type.Is(Type::OrderedNumber()) &&
3241 rhs_type.Is(truncation.IdentifiesZeroAndMinusZero()
3242 ? Type::OrderedNumber()
3243 : Type::PlainNumber())) {
3244 lowering->DoMin(node,
3245 lowering->machine()->Float64LessThanOrEqual(),
3246 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3247 } else {
3248 ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3249 }
3250 }
3251 }
3252 return;
3253 }
3254 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeNumberPow: {
3255 // Checked float64 ** float64 => float64
3256 VisitBinop<T>(node,
3257 UseInfo::CheckedNumberOrOddballAsFloat64(
3258 kDistinguishZeros, FeedbackSource()),
3259 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, Type::Number());
3260 if (lower<T>()) ChangeToPureOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3261 return;
3262 }
3263 case IrOpcode::kNumberAtan2:
3264 case IrOpcode::kNumberPow: {
3265 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
3266 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3267 if (lower<T>()) ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3268 return;
3269 }
3270 case IrOpcode::kNumberCeil:
3271 case IrOpcode::kNumberFloor:
3272 case IrOpcode::kNumberRound:
3273 case IrOpcode::kNumberTrunc: {
3274 // For NumberCeil, NumberFloor, NumberRound and NumberTrunc we propagate
3275 // the zero identification part of the truncation, and we turn them into
3276 // no-ops if we figure out (late) that their input is already an
3277 // integer, NaN or -0.
3278 Type const input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
3279 VisitUnop<T>(node,
3280 UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(truncation.identify_zeros()),
3281 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
3282 if (lower<T>()) {
3283 if (input_type.Is(type_cache_->kIntegerOrMinusZeroOrNaN)) {
3284 DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
3285 } else if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kNumberRound) {
3286 DeferReplacement(node, lowering->Float64Round(node));
3287 } else {
3288 ChangeOp(node, Float64Op(node));
3289 }
3290 }
3291 return;
3292 }
3293 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntAsIntN:
3294 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntAsUintN: {
3295 const bool is_asuintn =
3296 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntAsUintN;
3297 const auto p = SpeculativeBigIntAsNParametersOf(node->op());
3298 DCHECK_LE(0, p.bits());
3299 DCHECK_LE(p.bits(), 64);
3300
3301 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0,
3302 UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(p.feedback()));
3303 SetOutput<T>(
3304 node, MachineRepresentation::kWord64,
3305 is_asuintn ? Type::UnsignedBigInt64() : Type::SignedBigInt64());
3306 if (lower<T>()) {
3307 if (p.bits() == 0) {
3308 DeferReplacement(node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
3309 Type::UnsignedBigInt63(),
3310 jsgraph_->Int64Constant(0)));
3311 } else if (p.bits() == 64) {
3312 DeferReplacement(node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
3313 is_asuintn ? Type::UnsignedBigInt64()
3314 : Type::SignedBigInt64(),
3315 node->InputAt(0)));
3316 } else {
3317 if (is_asuintn) {
3318 const uint64_t mask = (1ULL << p.bits()) - 1ULL;
3319 ChangeUnaryToPureBinaryOp(node, lowering->machine()->Word64And(),
3320 1, jsgraph_->Int64Constant(mask));
3321 } else {
3322 // We truncate the value to N bits, but to correctly interpret
3323 // negative values, we have to fill the top (64-N) bits with the
3324 // sign. This is done by shifting the value left and then back
3325 // with an arithmetic right shift. E.g. for {value} =
3326 // 0..0'0001'1101 (29n) and N = 3: {shifted} is 1010'0000'0..0
3327 // after left shift by 61 bits, {unshifted} is 1..1'1111'1101
3328 // after arithmetic right shift by 61. This is the 64 bit
3329 // representation of -3 we expect for the signed 3 bit integer
3330 // 101.
3331 const uint64_t shift = 64 - p.bits();
3332 Node* value = node->InputAt(0);
3333 Node* shifted =
3334 graph()->NewNode(lowering->machine()->Word64Shl(), value,
3335 jsgraph_->Uint64Constant(shift));
3336 Node* unshifted =
3337 graph()->NewNode(lowering->machine()->Word64Sar(), shifted,
3338 jsgraph_->Uint64Constant(shift));
3339
3340 ReplaceWithPureNode(node, unshifted);
3341 }
3342 }
3343 }
3344 return;
3345 }
3346 case IrOpcode::kNumberAcos:
3347 case IrOpcode::kNumberAcosh:
3348 case IrOpcode::kNumberAsin:
3349 case IrOpcode::kNumberAsinh:
3350 case IrOpcode::kNumberAtan:
3351 case IrOpcode::kNumberAtanh:
3352 case IrOpcode::kNumberCos:
3353 case IrOpcode::kNumberCosh:
3354 case IrOpcode::kNumberExp:
3355 case IrOpcode::kNumberExpm1:
3356 case IrOpcode::kNumberLog:
3357 case IrOpcode::kNumberLog1p:
3358 case IrOpcode::kNumberLog2:
3359 case IrOpcode::kNumberLog10:
3360 case IrOpcode::kNumberCbrt:
3361 case IrOpcode::kNumberSin:
3362 case IrOpcode::kNumberSinh:

3400 return;

3402 case IrOpcode::kNumberToBoolean: {
3403 // For NumberToBoolean we don't care whether the input is 0 or
3404 // -0, since both of them are mapped to false anyways, so we
3405 // can generally pass kIdentifyZeros truncation.
3406 Type const input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));

3408 // 0, -0 and NaN all map to false, so we can safely truncate
3409 // all of them to zero here.

3415 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
3416 if (lower<T>()) lowering->DoOrderedNumberToBit(node);
3417 } else {

3419 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
3420 if (lower<T>()) lowering->DoNumberToBit(node);
3421 }

3423 }

3429 return;
3430 }

3519 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntAdd:
3520 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntSubtract:
3521 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntMultiply: {

3560 VisitUnused<T>(node);

3562 }
3563 BigIntOperationHint hint = BigIntOperationHintOf(node->op());
3564 switch (hint) {
3565 case BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt64: {
3566 VisitBinop<T>(
3567 node, UseInfo::CheckedBigInt64AsWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
3568 MachineRepresentation::kWord64, Type::SignedBigInt64());

3570 ChangeOp(node, Int64OverflowOp(node));

3573 }
3574 case BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt: {

3577 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
