3585 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntBitwiseAnd:
3586 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntBitwiseOr:
3587 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntBitwiseXor: {
3588 if (truncation.IsUnused() && BothInputsAre(node, Type::BigInt())) {
3589 VisitUnused<T>(node);
3590 return;
3591 }
3592 if (Is64() && truncation.IsUsedAsWord64()) {
3593 VisitBinop<T>(
3594 node, UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
3595 MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
3596 if (lower<T>()) {
3597 ChangeToPureOp(node, Int64Op(node));
3598 }
3599 return;
3600 }
3601 BigIntOperationHint hint = BigIntOperationHintOf(node->op());
3602 switch (hint) {
3603 case BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt64: {
3604 VisitBinop<T>(
3605 node, UseInfo::CheckedBigInt64AsWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
3606 MachineRepresentation::kWord64, Type::SignedBigInt64());
3607 if (lower<T>()) {
3608 ChangeToPureOp(node, Int64Op(node));
3609 }
3610 return;
3611 }
3612 case BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt: {
3613 VisitBinop<T>(
3614 node, UseInfo::CheckedBigIntAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource{}),
3615 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3616 if (lower<T>()) {
3617 ChangeOp(node, BigIntOp(node));
3618 }
3619 return;
3620 }
3621 }
3622 }
3623 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntShiftLeft:
3624 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntShiftRight: {
3625 if (truncation.IsUnused() && BothInputsAre(node, Type::BigInt())) {
3626 VisitUnused<T>(node);
3627 return;
3628 }
3629 if (Is64() && TryOptimizeBigInt64Shift<T>(node, truncation, lowering)) {
3630 return;
3631 }
3632 DCHECK_EQ(BigIntOperationHintOf(node->op()),
3633 BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt);
3634 VisitBinop<T>(node,
3635 UseInfo::CheckedBigIntAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource{}),
3636 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3637 if (lower<T>()) {
3638 ChangeOp(node, BigIntOp(node));
3639 }
3640 return;
3641 }
3642 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntEqual:
3643 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntLessThan:
3644 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntLessThanOrEqual: {
3645 // Loose equality can throw a TypeError when failing to cast an object
3646 // operand to primitive.
3647 if (truncation.IsUnused() && BothInputsAre(node, Type::BigInt())) {
3648 VisitUnused<T>(node);
3649 return;
3650 }
3651 BigIntOperationHint hint = BigIntOperationHintOf(node->op());
3652 switch (hint) {
3653 case BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt64: {
3654 VisitBinop<T>(node,
3655 UseInfo::CheckedBigInt64AsWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
3656 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
3657 if (lower<T>()) {
3658 ChangeToPureOp(node, Int64Op(node));
3659 }
3660 return;
3661 }
3662 case BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt: {
3663 VisitBinop<T>(
3664 node, UseInfo::CheckedBigIntAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource{}),
3665 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3666 if (lower<T>()) {
3667 ChangeToPureOp(node, BigIntOp(node));
3668 }
3669 return;
3670 }
3671 }
3672 }
3673 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeBigIntNegate: {
3674 // NOTE: If truncation is Unused, we still need to preserve at least the
3675 // BigInt type check (see http://crbug.com/1431713 for some details).
3676 // We can use the standard lowering to word64 operations and have
3677 // following phases remove the unused truncation and subtraction
3678 // operations.
3679 if (Is64() && truncation.IsUsedAsWord64()) {
3680 VisitUnop<T>(node,
3681 UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
3682 MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
3683 if (lower<T>()) {
3684 ChangeUnaryToPureBinaryOp(node, lowering->machine()->Int64Sub(), 0,
3685 jsgraph_->Int64Constant(0));
3686 }
3687 } else {
3688 VisitUnop<T>(node,
3689 UseInfo::CheckedBigIntAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource{}),
3690 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3691 if (lower<T>()) {
3692 ChangeToPureOp(node, lowering->simplified()->BigIntNegate());
3693 }
3694 }
3695 return;
3696 }
3697 case IrOpcode::kStringConcat: {
3698 // TODO(turbofan): We currently depend on having this first length input
3699 // to make sure that the overflow check is properly scheduled before the
3700 // actual string concatenation. We should also use the length to pass it
3701 // to the builtin or decide in optimized code how to construct the
3702 // resulting string (i.e. cons string or sequential string).
3703 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::TaggedSigned()); // length
3704 ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // first
3705 ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // second
3706 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3707 return;
3708 }
3709 case IrOpcode::kStringEqual:
3710 case IrOpcode::kStringLessThan:
3711 case IrOpcode::kStringLessThanOrEqual: {
3712 return VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
3713 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3714 }
3715 case IrOpcode::kStringCharCodeAt: {
3716 return VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), UseInfo::Word(),
3717 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3718 }
3719 case IrOpcode::kStringCodePointAt: {
3720 return VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), UseInfo::Word(),
3721 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3722 }
3723 case IrOpcode::kStringFromSingleCharCode: {
3724 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3725 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3726 return;
3727 }
3728 case IrOpcode::kStringFromSingleCodePoint: {
3729 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3730 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3731 return;
3732 }
3733 case IrOpcode::kStringFromCodePointAt: {
3734 return VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), UseInfo::Word(),
3735 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3736 }
3737 case IrOpcode::kStringIndexOf: {
3738 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
3739 ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
3740 ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::TaggedSigned());
3741 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned);
3742 return;
3743 }
3744 case IrOpcode::kStringLength:
3745 case IrOpcode::kStringWrapperLength: {
3746 // TODO(bmeurer): The input representation should be TaggedPointer.
3747 // Fix this once we have a dedicated StringConcat/JSStringAdd
3748 // operator, which marks it's output as TaggedPointer properly.
3749 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
3750 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3751 return;
3752 }
3753 case IrOpcode::kStringSubstring: {
3754 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
3755 ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32());
3756 ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32());
3757 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 3);
3758 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3759 return;
3760 }
3761 case IrOpcode::kStringToLowerCaseIntl:
3762 case IrOpcode::kStringToUpperCaseIntl: {
3763 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
3764 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3765 return;
3766 }
3767 case IrOpcode::kCheckBounds:
3768 return VisitCheckBounds<T>(node, lowering);
3769 case IrOpcode::kCheckHeapObject: {
3770 if (InputCannotBe(node, Type::SignedSmall())) {
3771 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
3772 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3773 } else {
3774 VisitUnop<T>(
3775 node, UseInfo::CheckedHeapObjectAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource()),
3776 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3777 }
3778 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
3779 return;
3780 }
3781 case IrOpcode::kCheckIf: {
3782 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Bool());
3783 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 1);
3784 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kNone);
3785 return;
3786 }
3787 case IrOpcode::kCheckInternalizedString: {
3788 VisitCheck<T>(node, Type::InternalizedString(), lowering);
3789 return;
3790 }
3791 case IrOpcode::kCheckNumber: {
3792 Type const input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
3793 if (input_type.Is(Type::Number())) {
3794 VisitNoop<T>(node, truncation);
3795 } else {
3796 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
3797 MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
3798 }
3799 return;
3800 }
3801 case IrOpcode::kCheckNumberFitsInt32: {
3802 Type const input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
3803 if (input_type.Is(Type::Signed32())) {
3804 VisitNoop<T>(node, truncation);
3805 } else {
3806 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
3807 MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
3808 }
3809 return;
3810 }
3811 case IrOpcode::kCheckReceiver: {
3812 VisitCheck<T>(node, Type::Receiver(), lowering);
3813 return;
3814 }
3815 case IrOpcode::kCheckReceiverOrNullOrUndefined: {
3816 VisitCheck<T>(node, Type::ReceiverOrNullOrUndefined(), lowering);
3817 return;
3818 }
3819 case IrOpcode::kCheckSmi: {
3820 const CheckParameters& params = CheckParametersOf(node->op());
3821 if (SmiValuesAre32Bits() && truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
3822 VisitUnop<T>(node,
3823 UseInfo::CheckedSignedSmallAsWord32(kDistinguishZeros,
3824 params.feedback()),
3825 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
3826 } else {
3827 VisitUnop<T>(
3828 node,
3829 UseInfo::CheckedSignedSmallAsTaggedSigned(params.feedback()),
3830 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned);
3831 }
3832 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
3833 return;
3834 }
3835 case IrOpcode::kCheckString: {
3836 const CheckParameters& params = CheckParametersOf(node->op());
3837 if (InputIs(node, Type::String())) {
3838 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
3839 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3840 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
3841 } else {
3842 VisitUnop<T>(
3843 node,
3844 UseInfo::CheckedHeapObjectAsTaggedPointer(params.feedback()),
3845 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3846 }
3847 return;
3848 }
3849 case IrOpcode::kCheckStringOrStringWrapper: {
3850 const CheckParameters& params = CheckParametersOf(node->op());
3851 if (InputIs(node, Type::StringOrStringWrapper())) {
3852 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
3853 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3854 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
3855 } else {
3856 VisitUnop<T>(
3857 node,
3858 UseInfo::CheckedHeapObjectAsTaggedPointer(params.feedback()),
3859 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3860 }
3861 return;
3862 }
3863 case IrOpcode::kCheckSymbol: {
3864 VisitCheck<T>(node, Type::Symbol(), lowering);
3865 return;
3866 }
3867
3868 case IrOpcode::kAllocate: {
3869 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Word());
3870 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 1);
3871 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
3872 return;
3873 }
3874 case IrOpcode::kLoadFramePointer: {
3875 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
3876 return;
3877 }
3878#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3879 case IrOpcode::kLoadStackPointer: {
3880 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
3881 return;
3882 }
3883 case IrOpcode::kSetStackPointer: {
3884 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kNone);
3885 return;
3886 }
3887#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3888 case IrOpcode::kLoadMessage: {
3889 if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
3890 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Word(), MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
3891 return;
3892 }
3893 case IrOpcode::kStoreMessage: {
3894 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Word());
3895 ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
3896 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 2);
3897 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kNone);
3898 return;
3899 }
3900 case IrOpcode::kLoadFieldByIndex: {
3901 if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
3902 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
3903 MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
3904 return;
3905 }
3906 case IrOpcode::kLoadField: {
3907 if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
3908 FieldAccess access = FieldAccessOf(node->op());
3909 MachineRepresentation const representation =
3910 access.machine_type.representation();
3911 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfoForBasePointer(access), representation);
3912 return;
3913 }
3914 case IrOpcode::kStoreField: {
3915 FieldAccess access = FieldAccessOf(node->op());
3916 Node* value_node = node->InputAt(1);
3917 NodeInfo* input_info = GetInfo(value_node);
3918 MachineRepresentation field_representation =
3919 access.machine_type.representation();
3920
3921 // Convert to Smi if possible, such that we can avoid a write barrier.
3922 if (field_representation == MachineRepresentation::kTagged &&
3923 TypeOf(value_node).Is(Type::SignedSmall())) {
3924 field_representation = MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned;
3925 }
3926 WriteBarrierKind write_barrier_kind = WriteBarrierKindFor(
3927 access.base_is_tagged, field_representation, access.offset,
3928 access.type, input_info->representation(), value_node);
3929
3930 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfoForBasePointer(access));
3931 ProcessInput<T>(
3932 node, 1, TruncatingUseInfoFromRepresentation(field_representation));
3933 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 2);
3934 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kNone);
3935 if (lower<T>()) {
3936 if (write_barrier_kind < access.write_barrier_kind) {
3937 access.write_barrier_kind = write_barrier_kind;
3938 ChangeOp(node, jsgraph_->simplified()->StoreField(access));
3939 }
3940 }
3941 return;
3942 }
3943 case IrOpcode::kLoadElement: {
3944 if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
3945 ElementAccess access = ElementAccessOf(node->op());
3946 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfoForBasePointer(access), UseInfo::Word(),
3947 access.machine_type.representation());
3948 return;
3949 }
3950 case IrOpcode::kLoadStackArgument: {
3951 if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
3952 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::Word(), MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
3953 return;
3954 }
3955 case IrOpcode::kStoreElement: {
3956 ElementAccess access = ElementAccessOf(node->op());
3957 Node* value_node = node->InputAt(2);
3958 NodeInfo* input_info = GetInfo(value_node);
3959 MachineRepresentation element_representation =
3960 access.machine_type.representation();
3961
3962 // Convert to Smi if possible, such that we can avoid a write barrier.
3963 if (element_representation == MachineRepresentation::kTagged &&
3964 TypeOf(value_node).Is(Type::SignedSmall())) {
3965 element_representation = MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned;
3966 }
3967 WriteBarrierKind write_barrier_kind = WriteBarrierKindFor(
3968 access.base_is_tagged, element_representation, access.type,
3969 input_info->representation(), value_node);
3970 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfoForBasePointer(access)); // base
3971 ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::Word()); // index
3972 ProcessInput<T>(node, 2,
3973 TruncatingUseInfoFromRepresentation(
3974 element_representation)); // value
3975 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 3);
3976 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kNone);
3977 if (lower<T>()) {
3978 if (write_barrier_kind < access.write_barrier_kind) {
3979 access.write_barrier_kind = write_barrier_kind;
3980 ChangeOp(node, jsgraph_->simplified()->StoreElement(access));
3981 }
3982 }
3983 return;
3984 }
3985 case IrOpcode::kNumberIsFloat64Hole: {
3986 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
3987 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
3988 return;
3989 }
3990 case IrOpcode::kTransitionAndStoreElement: {
3991 Type value_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(2));
3992
3993 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // array
3994 ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::Word()); // index
3995
3996 if (value_type.Is(Type::SignedSmall())) {
3997 ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32()); // value
3998 if (lower<T>()) {
3999 ChangeOp(node, simplified()->StoreSignedSmallElement());
4000 }
4001 } else if (value_type.Is(Type::Number())) {
4002 ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64()); // value
4003 if (lower<T>()) {
4004 MapRef double_map = DoubleMapParameterOf(node->op());
4005 ChangeOp(node,
4006 simplified()->TransitionAndStoreNumberElement(double_map));
4007 }
4008 } else if (value_type.Is(Type::NonNumber())) {
4009 ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // value
4010 if (lower<T>()) {
4011 MapRef fast_map = FastMapParameterOf(node->op());
4012 ChangeOp(node, simplified()->TransitionAndStoreNonNumberElement(
4013 fast_map, value_type));
4014 }
4015 } else {
4016 ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // value
4017 }
4018
4019 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 3);
4020 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4021 return;
4022 }
4023 case IrOpcode::kLoadTypedElement: {
4024 MachineRepresentation const rep =
4025 MachineRepresentationFromArrayType(ExternalArrayTypeOf(node->op()));
4026 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // buffer
4027 ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // base pointer
4028 ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::Word()); // external pointer
4029 ProcessInput<T>(node, 3, UseInfo::Word()); // index
4030 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 4);
4031 SetOutput<T>(node, rep);
4032 return;
4033 }
4034 case IrOpcode::kLoadDataViewElement: {
4035 MachineRepresentation const rep =
4036 MachineRepresentationFromArrayType(ExternalArrayTypeOf(node->op()));
4037 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // object
4038 ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::Word()); // base
4039 ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::Word()); // index
4040 ProcessInput<T>(node, 3, UseInfo::Bool()); // little-endian
4041 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 4);
4042 SetOutput<T>(node, rep);
4043 return;
4044 }
4045 case IrOpcode::kStoreTypedElement: {
4046 MachineRepresentation const rep =
4047 MachineRepresentationFromArrayType(ExternalArrayTypeOf(node->op()));
4048 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // buffer
4049 ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // base pointer
4050 ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::Word()); // external pointer
4051 ProcessInput<T>(node, 3, UseInfo::Word()); // index
4052 ProcessInput<T>(node, 4,
4053 TruncatingUseInfoFromRepresentation(rep)); // value
4054 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 5);
4055 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4056 return;
4057 }
4058 case IrOpcode::kStoreDataViewElement: {
4059 MachineRepresentation const rep =
4060 MachineRepresentationFromArrayType(ExternalArrayTypeOf(node->op()));
4061 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // object
4062 ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::Word()); // base
4063 ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::Word()); // index
4064 ProcessInput<T>(node, 3,
4065 TruncatingUseInfoFromRepresentation(rep)); // value
4066 ProcessInput<T>(node, 4, UseInfo::Bool()); // little-endian
4067 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 5);
4068 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4069 return;
4070 }
4071 case IrOpcode::kConvertReceiver: {
4072 Type input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
4073 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // object
4074 ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // native_context
4075 ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // global_proxy
4076 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 3);
4077 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4078 if (lower<T>()) {
4079 // Try to optimize the {node} based on the input type.
4080 if (input_type.Is(Type::Receiver())) {
4081 DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4082 } else if (input_type.Is(Type::NullOrUndefined())) {
4083 DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(2));
4084 } else if (!input_type.Maybe(Type::NullOrUndefined())) {
4085 ChangeOp(node, lowering->simplified()->ConvertReceiver(
4086 ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined));
4087 }
4088 }
4089 return;
4090 }
4091 case IrOpcode::kPlainPrimitiveToNumber: {
4092 if (InputIs(node, Type::Boolean())) {
4093 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Bool(), MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
4094 if (lower<T>()) {
4095 DeferReplacement(node, InsertSemanticsHintForVerifier(
4096 node->op(), node->InputAt(0)));
4097 }
4098 } else if (InputIs(node, Type::String())) {
4099 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4100 MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4101 if (lower<T>()) {
4102 ChangeOp(node, simplified()->StringToNumber());
4103 }
4104 } else if (truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
4105 if (InputIs(node, Type::NumberOrOddball())) {
4106 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
4107 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
4108 if (lower<T>()) {
4109 DeferReplacement(node, InsertSemanticsHintForVerifier(
4110 node->op(), node->InputAt(0)));
4111 }
4112 } else {
4113 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4114 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
4115 if (lower<T>()) {
4116 ChangeOp(node, simplified()->PlainPrimitiveToWord32());
4117 }
4118 }
4119 } else if (truncation.TruncatesOddballAndBigIntToNumber()) {
4120 if (InputIs(node, Type::NumberOrOddball())) {
4121 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4122 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
4123 if (lower<T>()) {
4124 DeferReplacement(node, InsertSemanticsHintForVerifier(
4125 node->op(), node->InputAt(0)));
4126 }
4127 } else {
4128 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4129 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
4130 if (lower<T>()) {
4131 ChangeOp(node, simplified()->PlainPrimitiveToFloat64());
4132 }
4133 }
4134 } else {
4135 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4136 MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4137 }
4138 return;
4139 }
4140 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeToNumber: {
4141 NumberOperationParameters const& p =
4142 NumberOperationParametersOf(node->op());
4143 switch (p.hint()) {
4144 case NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall:
4145 case NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmallInputs:
4146 VisitUnop<T>(node,
4147 CheckedUseInfoAsWord32FromHint(
4148 p.hint(), kDistinguishZeros, p.feedback()),
4149 MachineRepresentation::kWord32, Type::Signed32());
4150 break;
4151 case NumberOperationHint::kNumber:
4152 case NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrBoolean:
4153 case NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball:
4154 VisitUnop<T>(
4155 node, CheckedUseInfoAsFloat64FromHint(p.hint(), p.feedback()),
4156 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
4157 break;
4158 }
4159 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4160 return;
4161 }
4162 case IrOpcode::kSpeculativeToBigInt: {
4163 if (truncation.IsUnused() && InputIs(node, Type::BigInt())) {
4164 VisitUnused<T>(node);
4165 return;
4166 }
4167 if (Is64() && truncation.IsUsedAsWord64()) {
4168 VisitUnop<T>(node,
4169 UseInfo::CheckedBigIntTruncatingWord64(FeedbackSource{}),
4170 MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
4171 } else {
4172 BigIntOperationParameters const& p =
4173 BigIntOperationParametersOf(node->op());
4174 switch (p.hint()) {
4175 case BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt64: {
4176 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::CheckedBigInt64AsWord64(p.feedback()),
4177 MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
4178 break;
4179 }
4180 case BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt: {
4181 VisitUnop<T>(node,
4182 UseInfo::CheckedBigIntAsTaggedPointer(p.feedback()),
4183 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4184 }
4185 }
4186 }
4187 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4188 return;
4189 }
4190 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsArrayBufferView: {
4191 // TODO(turbofan): Introduce a Type::ArrayBufferView?
4192 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4193 return;
4194 }
4195 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsBigInt: {
4196 VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::BigInt(), lowering);
4197 return;
4198 }
4199 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsCallable: {
4200 VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::Callable(), lowering);
4201 return;
4202 }
4203 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsConstructor: {
4204 // TODO(turbofan): Introduce a Type::Constructor?
4205 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4206 return;
4207 }
4208 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsDetectableCallable: {
4209 VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::DetectableCallable(), lowering);
4210 return;
4211 }
4212 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsFiniteNumber: {
4213 Type const input_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0));
4214 if (input_type.Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger)) {
4215 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::None(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4216 if (lower<T>()) {
4217 DeferReplacement(
4218 node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4219 true_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(1)));
4220 }
4221 } else if (!input_type.Maybe(Type::Number())) {
4222 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Any(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4223 if (lower<T>()) {
4224 DeferReplacement(
4225 node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4226 false_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0)));
4227 }
4228 } else if (input_type.Is(Type::Number())) {
4229 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4230 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4231 if (lower<T>()) {
4232 ChangeOp(node, lowering->simplified()->NumberIsFinite());
4233 }
4234 } else {
4235 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4236 }
4237 return;
4238 }
4239 case IrOpcode::kNumberIsFinite: {
4240 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4241 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4242 return;
4243 }
4244 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsSafeInteger: {
4245 Type const input_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0));
4246 if (input_type.Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger)) {
4247 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::None(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4248 if (lower<T>()) {
4249 DeferReplacement(
4250 node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4251 true_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(1)));
4252 }
4253 } else if (!input_type.Maybe(Type::Number())) {
4254 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Any(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4255 if (lower<T>()) {
4256 DeferReplacement(
4257 node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4258 false_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0)));
4259 }
4260 } else if (input_type.Is(Type::Number())) {
4261 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4262 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4263 if (lower<T>()) {
4264 ChangeOp(node, lowering->simplified()->NumberIsSafeInteger());
4265 }
4266 } else {
4267 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4268 }
4269 return;
4270 }
4271 case IrOpcode::kNumberIsSafeInteger: {
4272 UNREACHABLE();
4273 }
4274 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsInteger: {
4275 Type const input_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0));
4276 if (input_type.Is(type_cache_->kSafeInteger)) {
4277 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::None(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4278 if (lower<T>()) {
4279 DeferReplacement(
4280 node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4281 true_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(1)));
4282 }
4283 } else if (!input_type.Maybe(Type::Number())) {
4284 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Any(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4285 if (lower<T>()) {
4286 DeferReplacement(
4287 node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4288 false_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0)));
4289 }
4290 } else if (input_type.Is(Type::Number())) {
4291 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4292 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4293 if (lower<T>()) {
4294 ChangeOp(node, lowering->simplified()->NumberIsInteger());
4295 }
4296 } else {
4297 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4298 }
4299 return;
4300 }
4301 case IrOpcode::kNumberIsInteger: {
4302 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4303 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4304 return;
4305 }
4306 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsMinusZero: {
4307 Type const input_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0));
4308 if (input_type.Is(Type::MinusZero())) {
4309 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::None(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4310 if (lower<T>()) {
4311 DeferReplacement(
4312 node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4313 true_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(1)));
4314 }
4315 } else if (!input_type.Maybe(Type::MinusZero())) {
4316 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Any(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4317 if (lower<T>()) {
4318 DeferReplacement(
4319 node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4320 false_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0)));
4321 }
4322 } else if (input_type.Is(Type::Number())) {
4323 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4324 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4325 if (lower<T>()) {
4326 ChangeOp(node, simplified()->NumberIsMinusZero());
4327 }
4328 } else {
4329 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4330 }
4331 return;
4332 }
4333 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsNaN: {
4334 Type const input_type = GetUpperBound(node->InputAt(0));
4335 if (input_type.Is(Type::NaN())) {
4336 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::None(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4337 if (lower<T>()) {
4338 DeferReplacement(
4339 node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4340 true_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(1)));
4341 }
4342 } else if (!input_type.Maybe(Type::NaN())) {
4343 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Any(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4344 if (lower<T>()) {
4345 DeferReplacement(
4346 node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4347 false_type(), lowering->jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0)));
4348 }
4349 } else if (input_type.Is(Type::Number())) {
4350 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4351 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4352 if (lower<T>()) {
4353 ChangeOp(node, simplified()->NumberIsNaN());
4354 }
4355 } else {
4356 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4357 }
4358 return;
4359 }
4360 case IrOpcode::kNumberIsNaN: {
4361 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4362 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4363 return;
4364 }
4365 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsNonCallable: {
4366 VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::NonCallable(), lowering);
4367 return;
4368 }
4369 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsNumber: {
4370 VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::Number(), lowering);
4371 return;
4372 }
4373 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsReceiver: {
4374 VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::Receiver(), lowering);
4375 return;
4376 }
4377 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsSmi: {
4378 // TODO(turbofan): Optimize based on input representation.
4379 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4380 return;
4381 }
4382 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsString: {
4383 VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::String(), lowering);
4384 return;
4385 }
4386 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsSymbol: {
4387 VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::Symbol(), lowering);
4388 return;
4389 }
4390 case IrOpcode::kObjectIsUndetectable: {
4391 VisitObjectIs<T>(node, Type::Undetectable(), lowering);
4392 return;
4393 }
4394 case IrOpcode::kArgumentsLength:
4395 case IrOpcode::kRestLength: {
4396 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned);
4397 return;
4398 }
4399 case IrOpcode::kNewDoubleElements:
4400 case IrOpcode::kNewSmiOrObjectElements: {
4401 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Word(),
4402 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4403 return;
4404 }
4405 case IrOpcode::kNewArgumentsElements: {
4406 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TaggedSigned(),
4407 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4408 return;
4409 }
4410 case IrOpcode::kCheckFloat64Hole: {
4411 Type const input_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
4412 CheckFloat64HoleMode mode =
4413 CheckFloat64HoleParametersOf(node->op()).mode();
4414 if (mode == CheckFloat64HoleMode::kAllowReturnHole) {
4415 // If {mode} is allow-return-hole _and_ the {truncation}
4416 // identifies NaN and undefined, we can just pass along
4417 // the {truncation} and completely wipe the {node}.
4418 if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
4419 if (truncation.TruncatesOddballAndBigIntToNumber()) {
4420 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4421 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
4422 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4423 return;
4424 }
4425 }
4426 VisitUnop<T>(
4427 node, UseInfo(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, Truncation::Any()),
4428 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, Type::Number());
4429 if (lower<T>() && input_type.Is(Type::Number())) {
4430 DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4431 }
4432 return;
4433 }
4434 case IrOpcode::kChangeFloat64HoleToTagged: {
4435 // If the {truncation} identifies NaN and undefined, we can just pass
4436 // along the {truncation} and completely wipe the {node}.
4437 if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
4438 if (truncation.TruncatesOddballAndBigIntToNumber()) {
4439 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4440 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
4441 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4442 return;
4443 }
4444 VisitUnop<T>(
4445 node, UseInfo(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, Truncation::Any()),
4446 MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4447 return;
4448 }
4449 case IrOpcode::kCheckNotTaggedHole: {
4450 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4451 MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4452 return;
4453 }
4454 case IrOpcode::kCheckClosure: {
4455 VisitUnop<T>(
4456 node, UseInfo::CheckedHeapObjectAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource()),
4457 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4458 return;
4459 }
4460 case IrOpcode::kConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined: {
4461 if (InputIs(node, Type::NumberOrHole()) &&
4462 truncation.IsUsedAsWord32()) {
4463 // Propagate the Word32 truncation.
4464 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
4465 MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
4466 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4467 } else if (InputIs(node, Type::NumberOrHole()) &&
4468 truncation.TruncatesOddballAndBigIntToNumber()) {
4469 // Propagate the Float64 truncation.
4470 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::TruncatingFloat64(),
4471 MachineRepresentation::kFloat64);
4472 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4473 } else if (InputIs(node, Type::NonInternal())) {
4474 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4475 MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4476 if (lower<T>()) DeferReplacement(node, node->InputAt(0));
4477 } else {
4478 // TODO(turbofan): Add a (Tagged) truncation that identifies hole
4479 // and undefined, i.e. for a[i] === obj cases.
4480 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4481 MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4482 }
4483 return;
4484 }
4485 case IrOpcode::kCheckEqualsSymbol:
4486 case IrOpcode::kCheckEqualsInternalizedString:
4487 return VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4488 MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4489 case IrOpcode::kMapGuard:
4490 // Eliminate MapGuard nodes here.
4491 return VisitUnused<T>(node);
4492 case IrOpcode::kCheckMaps: {
4493 CheckMapsParameters const& p = CheckMapsParametersOf(node->op());
4494 return VisitUnop<T>(
4495 node, UseInfo::CheckedHeapObjectAsTaggedPointer(p.feedback()),
4496 MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4497 }
4498 case IrOpcode::kTransitionElementsKind: {
4499 return VisitUnop<T>(
4500 node, UseInfo::CheckedHeapObjectAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource()),
4501 MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4502 }
4503 case IrOpcode::kTransitionElementsKindOrCheckMap: {
4504 return VisitUnop<T>(
4505 node, UseInfo::CheckedHeapObjectAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource()),
4506 MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4507 }
4508 case IrOpcode::kCompareMaps:
4509 return VisitUnop<T>(
4510 node, UseInfo::CheckedHeapObjectAsTaggedPointer(FeedbackSource()),
4511 MachineRepresentation::kBit);
4512 case IrOpcode::kEnsureWritableFastElements:
4513 return VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4514 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4515 case IrOpcode::kMaybeGrowFastElements: {
4516 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // object
4517 ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::AnyTagged()); // elements
4518 ProcessInput<T>(node, 2, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32()); // index
4519 ProcessInput<T>(node, 3, UseInfo::TruncatingWord32()); // length
4520 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 4);
4521 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4522 return;
4523 }
4524
4525 case IrOpcode::kDateNow:
4526 VisitInputs<T>(node);
4527 return SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4528 case IrOpcode::kDoubleArrayMax: {
4529 return VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4530 MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4531 }
4532 case IrOpcode::kDoubleArrayMin: {
4533 return VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4534 MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4535 }
4536 case IrOpcode::kFrameState:
4537 return VisitFrameState<T>(FrameState{node});
4538 case IrOpcode::kStateValues:
4539 return VisitStateValues<T>(node);
4540 case IrOpcode::kObjectState:
4541 return VisitObjectState<T>(node);
4542 case IrOpcode::kObjectId:
4543 return SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4544
4545 case IrOpcode::kTypeGuard: {
4546 if (truncation.IsUnused()) return VisitUnused<T>(node);
4547
4548 // We just get rid of the sigma here, choosing the best representation
4549 // for the sigma's type.
4550 Type type = TypeOf(node);
4551 MachineRepresentation representation =
4552 GetOutputInfoForPhi(type, truncation);
4553
4554 // Here we pretend that the input has the sigma's type for the
4555 // conversion.
4556 UseInfo use(representation, truncation);
4557 if (propagate<T>()) {
4558 EnqueueInput<T>(node, 0, use);
4559 } else if (lower<T>()) {
4560 ConvertInput(node, 0, use, type);
4561 }
4562 ProcessRemainingInputs<T>(node, 1);
4563 SetOutput<T>(node, representation);
4564 return;
4565 }
4566
4567 case IrOpcode::kFinishRegion:
4568 VisitInputs<T>(node);
4569 // Assume the output is tagged pointer.
4570 return SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer);
4571
4572 case IrOpcode::kReturn:
4573 VisitReturn<T>(node);
4574 // Assume the output is tagged.
4575 return SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4576
4577 case IrOpcode::kFindOrderedHashMapEntry: {
4578 Type const key_type = TypeOf(node->InputAt(1));
4579 if (key_type.Is(Type::Signed32OrMinusZero())) {
4580 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), UseInfo::TruncatingWord32(),
4581 MachineType::PointerRepresentation());
4582 if (lower<T>()) {
4583 ChangeOp(
4584 node,
4585 lowering->simplified()->FindOrderedHashMapEntryForInt32Key());
4586 }
4587 } else {
4588 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4589 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned);
4590 }
4591 return;
4592 }
4593
4594 case IrOpcode::kFindOrderedHashSetEntry:
4595 VisitBinop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4596 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned);
4597 return;
4598
4599 case IrOpcode::kFastApiCall: {
4600 VisitFastApiCall<T>(node, lowering);
4601 return;
4602 }
4603
4604 // Operators with all inputs tagged and no or tagged output have uniform
4605 // handling.
4606 case IrOpcode::kEnd:
4607 case IrOpcode::kIfSuccess:
4608 case IrOpcode::kIfException:
4609 case IrOpcode::kIfTrue:
4610 case IrOpcode::kIfFalse:
4611 case IrOpcode::kIfValue:
4612 case IrOpcode::kIfDefault:
4613 case IrOpcode::kDeoptimize:
4614 case IrOpcode::kEffectPhi:
4615 case IrOpcode::kTerminate:
4616 case IrOpcode::kCheckpoint:
4617 case IrOpcode::kLoop:
4618 case IrOpcode::kMerge:
4619 case IrOpcode::kThrow:
4620 case IrOpcode::kBeginRegion:
4621 case IrOpcode::kProjection:
4622 case IrOpcode::kOsrValue:
4623 case IrOpcode::kArgumentsElementsState:
4624 case IrOpcode::kArgumentsLengthState:
4625 case IrOpcode::kUnreachable:
4626 case IrOpcode::kRuntimeAbort:
4627// All JavaScript operators except JSToNumber, JSToNumberConvertBigInt,
4628// kJSToNumeric and JSWasmCall have uniform handling.
4629#define OPCODE_CASE(name, ...) case IrOpcode::k##name:
4630 JS_SIMPLE_BINOP_LIST(OPCODE_CASE)
4631 JS_OBJECT_OP_LIST(OPCODE_CASE)
4632 JS_CONTEXT_OP_LIST(OPCODE_CASE)
4633 JS_OTHER_OP_LIST(OPCODE_CASE)
4634#undef OPCODE_CASE
4635 case IrOpcode::kJSBitwiseNot:
4636 case IrOpcode::kJSDecrement:
4637 case IrOpcode::kJSIncrement:
4638 case IrOpcode::kJSNegate:
4639 case IrOpcode::kJSToLength:
4640 case IrOpcode::kJSToName:
4641 case IrOpcode::kJSToObject:
4642 case IrOpcode::kJSToString:
4643 case IrOpcode::kJSParseInt:
4644#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4645 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSWasmCall) {
4646 return VisitJSWasmCall<T>(node, lowering);
4647 }
4648#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4649 VisitInputs<T>(node);
4650 // Assume the output is tagged.
4651 return SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4652 case IrOpcode::kDeadValue:
4653 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Any());
4654 return SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4655 case IrOpcode::kStaticAssert:
4656 DCHECK(TypeOf(node->InputAt(0)).Is(Type::Boolean()));
4657 return VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::Bool(),
4658 MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4659 case IrOpcode::kAssertType:
4660 return VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(),
4661 MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4662 case IrOpcode::kVerifyType: {
4663 Type inputType = TypeOf(node->InputAt(0));
4664 VisitUnop<T>(node, UseInfo::AnyTagged(), MachineRepresentation::kTagged,
4665 inputType);
4666 if (lower<T>()) {
4667 if (inputType.CanBeAsserted()) {
4668 ChangeOp(node, simplified()->AssertType(inputType));
4669 } else {
4670 if (!v8_flags.fuzzing) {
4671#ifdef DEBUG
4672 inputType.Print();
4673#endif
4674 FATAL("%%VerifyType: unsupported type");
4675 }
4676 DisconnectFromEffectAndControl(node);
4677 }
4678 }
4679 return;
4680 }
4681 case IrOpcode::kCheckTurboshaftTypeOf: {
4682 NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node->InputAt(0));
4683 MachineRepresentation input_rep = info->representation();
4684 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo{input_rep, Truncation::None()});
4685 ProcessInput<T>(node, 1, UseInfo::Any());
4686 SetOutput<T>(node, input_rep);
4687 return;
4688 }
4689 case IrOpcode::kDebugBreak:
4690 return;
4691
4692 // Nodes from machine graphs.
4693 case IrOpcode::kEnterMachineGraph: {
4694 DCHECK_EQ(1, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
4695 UseInfo use_info = OpParameter<UseInfo>(node->op());
4696 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, use_info);
4697 SetOutput<T>(node, use_info.representation());
4698 if (lower<T>()) {
4699 DeferReplacement(node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4700 Type::Machine(), node->InputAt(0)));
4701 }
4702 return;
4703 }
4704 case IrOpcode::kExitMachineGraph: {
4705 DCHECK_EQ(1, node->op()->ValueInputCount());
4706 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::Any());
4707 const auto& p = ExitMachineGraphParametersOf(node->op());
4708 SetOutput<T>(node, p.output_representation(), p.output_type());
4709 if (lower<T>()) {
4710 DeferReplacement(node, InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(
4711 p.output_type(), node->InputAt(0)));
4712 }
4713 return;
4714 }
4715 case IrOpcode::kInt32Add:
4716 case IrOpcode::kInt32LessThanOrEqual:
4717 case IrOpcode::kInt32Sub:
4718 case IrOpcode::kUint32LessThan:
4719 case IrOpcode::kUint32LessThanOrEqual:
4720 case IrOpcode::kUint64LessThan:
4721 case IrOpcode::kUint64LessThanOrEqual:
4722 case IrOpcode::kUint32Div:
4723 case IrOpcode::kWord32And:
4724 case IrOpcode::kWord32Equal:
4725 case IrOpcode::kWord32Or:
4726 case IrOpcode::kWord32Shl:
4727 case IrOpcode::kWord32Shr:
4728 for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCount(); ++i) {
4729 ProcessInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::Any());
4730 }
4731 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord32);
4732 return;
4733 case IrOpcode::kInt64Add:
4734 case IrOpcode::kInt64Sub:
4735 case IrOpcode::kUint64Div:
4736 case IrOpcode::kWord64And:
4737 case IrOpcode::kWord64Shl:
4738 case IrOpcode::kWord64Shr:
4739 case IrOpcode::kChangeUint32ToUint64:
4740 for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCount(); ++i) {
4741 ProcessInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::Any());
4742 }
4743 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kWord64);
4744 return;
4745 case IrOpcode::kLoad:
4746 for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCount(); ++i) {
4747 ProcessInput<T>(node, i, UseInfo::Any());
4748 }
4749 SetOutput<T>(node, LoadRepresentationOf(node->op()).representation());
4750 return;
4751
4752#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
4753 case IrOpcode::kGetContinuationPreservedEmbedderData:
4754 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
4755 return;
4756
4757 case IrOpcode::kSetContinuationPreservedEmbedderData:
4758 ProcessInput<T>(node, 0, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
4759 SetOutput<T>(node, MachineRepresentation::kNone);
4760 return;
4761#endif // V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
4762
4763 default:
4764 FATAL(
4765 "Representation inference: unsupported opcode %i (%s), node #%i\n.",
4766 node->opcode(), node->op()->mnemonic(), node->id());
4767 break;
4768 }
4769 UNREACHABLE();
4770 }
4771
4772 void DisconnectFromEffectAndControl(Node* node) {
4773 if (node->op()->EffectInputCount() == 1) {
4774 Node* control;
4775 if (node->op()->ControlInputCount() == 1) {
4776 control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
4777 } else {
4778 DCHECK_EQ(node->op()->ControlInputCount(), 0);
4779 control = nullptr;
4780 }
4781 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
4782 ReplaceEffectControlUses(node, effect, control);
4783 } else {
4784 DCHECK_EQ(0, node->op()->EffectInputCount());
4785 DCHECK_EQ(0, node->op()->ControlOutputCount());
4786 DCHECK_EQ(0, node->op()->EffectOutputCount());
4787 }
4788 }
4789
4790 void DeferReplacement(Node* node, Node* replacement) {
4791 TRACE("defer replacement #%d:%s with #%d:%s\n", node->id(),
4792 node->op()->mnemonic(), replacement->id(),
4793 replacement->op()->mnemonic());
4794
4795 DisconnectFromEffectAndControl(node);
4796 node->NullAllInputs(); // Node is now dead.
4797
4798 replacements_.push_back(node);
4799 replacements_.push_back(replacement);
4800
4801 NotifyNodeReplaced(node, replacement);
4802 }
4803
4804 Node* InsertTypeOverrideForVerifier(const Type& type, Node* node) {
4805 if (V8_UNLIKELY(verification_enabled())) {
4806 DCHECK(!type.IsInvalid());
4807 node = graph()->NewNode(common()->SLVerifierHint(nullptr, type), node);
4808 verifier_->RecordHint(node);
4809 }
4810 return node;
4811 }
4812
4813 Node* InsertSemanticsHintForVerifier(const Operator* semantics, Node* node) {
4814 if (V8_UNLIKELY(verification_enabled())) {
4815 node = graph()->NewNode(common()->SLVerifierHint(semantics, {}), node);
4816 verifier_->RecordHint(node);
4817 }
4818 return node;
4819 }
4820
4821 private:
4822 void ChangeOp(Node* node, const Operator* new_op) {
4823 compiler::NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, new_op);
4824
4825 if (V8_UNLIKELY(observe_node_manager_ != nullptr))
4826 observe_node_manager_->OnNodeChanged(kSimplifiedLoweringReducerName, node,
4827 node);
4828 }
4829
4830 void NotifyNodeReplaced(Node* node, Node* replacement) {
4831 if (V8_UNLIKELY(observe_node_manager_ != nullptr))
4832 observe_node_manager_->OnNodeChanged(kSimplifiedLoweringReducerName, node,
4833 replacement);
4834 }
4835
4836 Type true_type() const { return singleton_true_; }
4837 Type false_type() const { return singleton_false_; }
4838
4839 JSGraph* jsgraph_;
4840 JSHeapBroker* broker_;
4841 Zone* zone_; // Temporary zone.
4842 // Map from node to its uses that might need to be revisited.
4843 ZoneMap<Node*, ZoneVector<Node*>> might_need_revisit_;
4844 size_t count_; // number of nodes in the graph
4845 ZoneVector<NodeInfo> info_; // node id -> usage information
4846#ifdef DEBUG
4847 ZoneVector<InputUseInfos> node_input_use_infos_; // Debug information about
4848 // requirements on inputs.
4849#endif // DEBUG
4850 NodeVector replacements_; // replacements to be done after lowering
4851 RepresentationChanger* changer_; // for inserting representation changes
4852 ZoneQueue<Node*> revisit_queue_; // Queue for revisiting nodes.
4853
4854 struct NodeState {
4855 Node* node;
4856 int input_index;
4857 };
4858 NodeVector traversal_nodes_; // Order in which to traverse the nodes.
4859 // TODO(danno): RepresentationSelector shouldn't know anything about the
4860 // source positions table, but must for now since there currently is no other
4861 // way to pass down source position information to nodes created during
4862 // lowering. Once this phase becomes a vanilla reducer, it should get source
4863 // position information via the SourcePositionWrapper like all other reducers.
4864 SourcePositionTable* source_positions_;
4865 NodeOriginTable* node_origins_;
4866 TypeCache const* type_cache_;
4867 OperationTyper op_typer_; // helper for the feedback typer
4868 Type singleton_true_;
4869 Type singleton_false_;
4870 TickCounter* const tick_counter_;
4871 Linkage* const linkage_;
4872 ObserveNodeManager* const observe_node_manager_;
4873 SimplifiedLoweringVerifier* verifier_; // Used to verify output graph.
4874
4875 NodeInfo* GetInfo(Node* node) {
4876 DCHECK(node->id() < count_);
4877 return &info_[node->id()];
4878 }
4879 Zone* zone() { return zone_; }
4880 Zone* graph_zone() { return jsgraph_->zone(); }
4881 Linkage* linkage() { return linkage_; }
4882};
4883
4884// Template specializations
4885
4886// Enqueue {use_node}'s {index} input if the {use_info} contains new information
4887// for that input node.
4888template <>
4889void RepresentationSelector::EnqueueInput<PROPAGATE>(Node* use_node, int index,
4890 UseInfo use_info) {
4891 Node* node = use_node->InputAt(index);
4892 NodeInfo* info = GetInfo(node);
4893#ifdef DEBUG
4894 // Check monotonicity of input requirements.
4895 node_input_use_infos_[use_node->id()].SetAndCheckInput(use_node, index,
4896 use_info);
4897#endif // DEBUG
4898 if (info->unvisited()) {
4899 info->AddUse(use_info);
4900 TRACE(" initial #%i: %s\n", node->id(), info->truncation().description());
4901 return;
4902 }
4903 TRACE(" queue #%i?: %s\n", node->id(), info->truncation().description());
4904 if (info->AddUse(use_info)) {
4905 // New usage information for the node is available.
4906 if (!info->queued()) {
4907 DCHECK(info->visited());
4908 revisit_queue_.push(node);
4909 info->set_queued();
4910 TRACE(" added: %s\n", info->truncation().description());
4911 } else {
4912 TRACE(" inqueue: %s\n", info->truncation().description());
4913 }
4914 }
4915}
4916
4917template <>
4918void RepresentationSelector::SetOutput<PROPAGATE>(
4919 Node* node, MachineRepresentation representation, Type restriction_type) {
4920 NodeInfo* const info = GetInfo(node);
4921 info->set_restriction_type(restriction_type);
4922}
4923
4924template <>
4925void RepresentationSelector::SetOutput<RETYPE>(
4926 Node* node, MachineRepresentation representation, Type restriction_type) {
4927 NodeInfo* const info = GetInfo(node);
4928 DCHECK(restriction_type.Is(info->restriction_type()));
4929 info->set_output(representation);
4930}
4931
4932template <>
4933void RepresentationSelector::SetOutput<LOWER>(
4934 Node* node, MachineRepresentation representation, Type restriction_type) {
4935 NodeInfo* const info = GetInfo(node);
4936 DCHECK_EQ(info->representation(), representation);
4937 DCHECK(restriction_type.Is(info->restriction_type()));
4938 USE(info);
4939}
4940
4941template <>
4942void RepresentationSelector::ProcessInput<PROPAGATE>(Node* node, int index,
4943 UseInfo use) {
4944 DCHECK_IMPLIES(use.type_check() != TypeCheckKind::kNone,
4945 !node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kNoDeopt) &&
4946 node->op()->EffectInputCount() > 0);
4947 EnqueueInput<PROPAGATE>(node, index, use);
4948}
4949
4950template <>
4951void RepresentationSelector::ProcessInput<RETYPE>(Node* node, int index,
4952 UseInfo use) {
4953 DCHECK_IMPLIES(use.type_check() != TypeCheckKind::kNone,
4954 !node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kNoDeopt) &&
4955 node->op()->EffectInputCount() > 0);
4956}
4957
4958template <>
4959void RepresentationSelector::ProcessInput<LOWER>(Node* node, int index,
4960 UseInfo use) {
4961 DCHECK_IMPLIES(use.type_check() != TypeCheckKind::kNone,
4962 !node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kNoDeopt) &&
4963 node->op()->EffectInputCount() > 0);
4964 ConvertInput(node, index, use);
4965}
4966
4967template <>
4968void RepresentationSelector::ProcessRemainingInputs<PROPAGATE>(Node* node,
4969 int index) {
4970 DCHECK_GE(index, NodeProperties::PastContextIndex(node));
4971
4972 // Enqueue other inputs (effects, control).
4973 for (int i = std::max(index, NodeProperties::FirstEffectIndex(node));
4974 i < node->InputCount(); ++i) {
4975 EnqueueInput<PROPAGATE>(node, i);
4976 }
4977}
4978
4979// The default, most general visitation case. For {node}, process all value,
4980// context, frame state, effect, and control inputs, assuming that value
4981// inputs should have {kRepTagged} representation and can observe all output
4982// values {kTypeAny}.
4983template <>
4984void RepresentationSelector::VisitInputs<PROPAGATE>(Node* node) {
4985 int first_effect_index = NodeProperties::FirstEffectIndex(node);
4986 // Visit value, context and frame state inputs as tagged.
4987 for (int i = 0; i < first_effect_index; i++) {
4988 ProcessInput<PROPAGATE>(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
4989 }
4990 // Only enqueue other inputs (effects, control).
4991 for (int i = first_effect_index; i < node->InputCount(); i++) {
4992 EnqueueInput<PROPAGATE>(node, i);
4993 }
4994}
4995
4996template <>
4997void RepresentationSelector::VisitInputs<LOWER>(Node* node) {
4998 int first_effect_index = NodeProperties::FirstEffectIndex(node);
4999 // Visit value, context and frame state inputs as tagged.
5000 for (int i = 0; i < first_effect_index; i++) {
5001 ProcessInput<LOWER>(node, i, UseInfo::AnyTagged());
5002 }
5003}
5004
5005template <>
5006void RepresentationSelector::InsertUnreachableIfNecessary<LOWER>(Node* node) {
5007 // If the node is effectful and it produces an impossible value, then we
5008 // insert Unreachable node after it.
5009 if (node->op()->ValueOutputCount() > 0 &&
5010 node->op()->EffectOutputCount() > 0 &&
5011 node->opcode() != IrOpcode::kUnreachable && TypeOf(node).IsNone()) {
5012 Node* control = (node->op()->ControlOutputCount() == 0)
5013 ? NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node, 0)
5014 : NodeProperties::FindSuccessfulControlProjection(node);
5015
5016 Node* unreachable =
5017 graph()->NewNode(common()->Unreachable(), node, control);
5018
5019 // Insert unreachable node and replace all the effect uses of the {node}
5020 // with the new unreachable node.
5021 for (Edge edge : node->use_edges()) {
5022 if (!NodeProperties::IsEffectEdge(edge)) continue;
5023 // Make sure to not overwrite the unreachable node's input. That would
5024 // create a cycle.
5025 if (edge.from() == unreachable) continue;
5026 // Avoid messing up the exceptional path.
5027 if (edge.from()->opcode() == IrOpcode::kIfException) {
5028 DCHECK(!node->op()->HasProperty(Operator::kNoThrow));
5029 DCHECK_EQ(NodeProperties::GetControlInput(edge.from()), node);
5030 continue;
5031 }
5032
5033 edge.UpdateTo(unreachable);
5034 }
5035 }
5036}
5037
5038SimplifiedLowering::SimplifiedLowering(
5039 JSGraph* jsgraph, JSHeapBroker* broker, Zone* zone,
5040 SourcePositionTable* source_positions, NodeOriginTable* node_origins,
5041 TickCounter* tick_counter, Linkage* linkage, OptimizedCompilationInfo* info,
5042 ObserveNodeManager* observe_node_manager)
5043 : jsgraph_(jsgraph),
5044 broker_(broker),
5045 zone_(zone),
5046 type_cache_(TypeCache::Get()),
5047 source_positions_(source_positions),
5048 node_origins_(node_origins),
5049 tick_counter_(tick_counter),
5050 linkage_(linkage),
5051 info_(info),
5052 observe_node_manager_(observe_node_manager) {}
5053
5054void SimplifiedLowering::LowerAllNodes() {
5055 SimplifiedLoweringVerifier* verifier = nullptr;
5056 if (v8_flags.verify_simplified_lowering) {
5057 verifier = zone_->New<SimplifiedLoweringVerifier>(zone_, graph());
5058 }
5059 RepresentationChanger changer(jsgraph(), broker_, verifier);
5060 RepresentationSelector selector(
5061 jsgraph(), broker_, zone_, &changer, source_positions_, node_origins_,
5062 tick_counter_, linkage_, observe_node_manager_, verifier);
5063 selector.Run(this);
5064}
5065
5066void SimplifiedLowering::DoJSToNumberOrNumericTruncatesToFloat64(
5067 Node* node, RepresentationSelector* selector) {
5068 DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumber ||
5069 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumberConvertBigInt ||
5070 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumeric);
5071 Node* value = node->InputAt(0);
5072 Node* context = node->InputAt(1);
5073 Node* frame_state = node->InputAt(2);
5074 Node* effect = node->InputAt(3);
5075 Node* control = node->InputAt(4);
5076
5077 Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), value);
5078 Node* branch0 = graph()->NewNode(
5079 common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check0,
5080 control);
5081
5082 Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
5083 Node* etrue0 = effect;
5084 Node* vtrue0;
5085 {
5086 vtrue0 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ChangeTaggedSignedToInt32(), value);
5087 vtrue0 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->ChangeInt32ToFloat64(), vtrue0);
5088 }
5089
5090 Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
5091 Node* efalse0 = effect;
5092 Node* vfalse0;
5093 {
5094 Operator const* op =
5095 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumber
5096 ? (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumberConvertBigInt
5097 ? ToNumberConvertBigIntOperator()
5098 : ToNumberOperator())
5099 : ToNumericOperator();
5100 Node* code = node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumber
5101 ? ToNumberCode()
5102 : (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumberConvertBigInt
5103 ? ToNumberConvertBigIntCode()
5104 : ToNumericCode());
5105 vfalse0 = efalse0 = if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(
5106 op, code, value, context, frame_state, efalse0, if_false0);
5107
5108 // Update potential {IfException} uses of {node} to point to the above
5109 // stub call node instead.
5110 Node* on_exception = nullptr;
5111 if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
5112 NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(on_exception, vfalse0);
5113 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(on_exception, efalse0);
5114 if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), vfalse0);
5115 }
5116
5117 Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), vfalse0);
5118 Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(
5119 common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check1,
5120 if_false0);
5121
5122 Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1);
5123 Node* etrue1 = efalse0;
5124 Node* vtrue1;
5125 {
5126 vtrue1 =
5127 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ChangeTaggedSignedToInt32(), vfalse0);
5128 vtrue1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->ChangeInt32ToFloat64(), vtrue1);
5129 }
5130
5131 Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
5132 Node* efalse1 = efalse0;
5133 Node* vfalse1;
5134 {
5135 vfalse1 = efalse1 = graph()->NewNode(
5136 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberValue()), efalse0,
5137 efalse1, if_false1);
5138 }
5139
5140 if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true1, if_false1);
5141 efalse0 =
5142 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue1, efalse1, if_false0);
5143 vfalse0 =
5144 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, 2),
5145 vtrue1, vfalse1, if_false0);
5146 }
5147
5148 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true0, if_false0);
5149 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue0, efalse0, control);
5150 value = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64, 2),
5151 vtrue0, vfalse0, control);
5152
5153 // Replace effect and control uses appropriately.
5154 for (Edge edge : node->use_edges()) {
5155 if (NodeProperties::IsControlEdge(edge)) {
5156 if (edge.from()->opcode() == IrOpcode::kIfSuccess) {
5157 edge.from()->ReplaceUses(control);
5158 edge.from()->Kill();
5159 } else {
5160 DCHECK_NE(IrOpcode::kIfException, edge.from()->opcode());
5161 edge.UpdateTo(control);
5162 }
5163 } else if (NodeProperties::IsEffectEdge(edge)) {
5164 edge.UpdateTo(effect);
5165 }
5166 }
5167
5168 selector->DeferReplacement(node, value);
5169}
5170
5171void SimplifiedLowering::DoJSToNumberOrNumericTruncatesToWord32(
5172 Node* node, RepresentationSelector* selector) {
5173 DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumber ||
5174 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumberConvertBigInt ||
5175 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumeric);
5176 Node* value = node->InputAt(0);
5177 Node* context = node->InputAt(1);
5178 Node* frame_state = node->InputAt(2);
5179 Node* effect = node->InputAt(3);
5180 Node* control = node->InputAt(4);
5181
5182 Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), value);
5183 Node* branch0 = graph()->NewNode(
5184 common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check0,
5185 control);
5186
5187 Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
5188 Node* etrue0 = effect;
5189 Node* vtrue0 =
5190 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ChangeTaggedSignedToInt32(), value);
5191
5192 Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
5193 Node* efalse0 = effect;
5194 Node* vfalse0;
5195 {
5196 Operator const* op =
5197 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumber
5198 ? (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumberConvertBigInt
5199 ? ToNumberConvertBigIntOperator()
5200 : ToNumberOperator())
5201 : ToNumericOperator();
5202 Node* code = node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumber
5203 ? ToNumberCode()
5204 : (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToNumberConvertBigInt
5205 ? ToNumberConvertBigIntCode()
5206 : ToNumericCode());
5207 vfalse0 = efalse0 = if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(
5208 op, code, value, context, frame_state, efalse0, if_false0);
5209
5210 // Update potential {IfException} uses of {node} to point to the above
5211 // stub call node instead.
5212 Node* on_exception = nullptr;
5213 if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &on_exception)) {
5214 NodeProperties::ReplaceControlInput(on_exception, vfalse0);
5215 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(on_exception, efalse0);
5216 if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), vfalse0);
5217 }
5218
5219 Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), vfalse0);
5220 Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(
5221 common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check1,
5222 if_false0);
5223
5224 Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1);
5225 Node* etrue1 = efalse0;
5226 Node* vtrue1 =
5227 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ChangeTaggedSignedToInt32(), vfalse0);
5228
5229 Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
5230 Node* efalse1 = efalse0;
5231 Node* vfalse1;
5232 {
5233 vfalse1 = efalse1 = graph()->NewNode(
5234 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberValue()), efalse0,
5235 efalse1, if_false1);
5236 vfalse1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->TruncateFloat64ToWord32(), vfalse1);
5237 }
5238
5239 if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true1, if_false1);
5240 efalse0 =
5241 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue1, efalse1, if_false0);
5242 vfalse0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, 2),
5243 vtrue1, vfalse1, if_false0);
5244 }
5245
5246 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true0, if_false0);
5247 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue0, efalse0, control);
5248 value = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, 2),
5249 vtrue0, vfalse0, control);
5250
5251 // Replace effect and control uses appropriately.
5252 for (Edge edge : node->use_edges()) {
5253 if (NodeProperties::IsControlEdge(edge)) {
5254 if (edge.from()->opcode() == IrOpcode::kIfSuccess) {
5255 edge.from()->ReplaceUses(control);
5256 edge.from()->Kill();
5257 } else {
5258 DCHECK_NE(IrOpcode::kIfException, edge.from()->opcode());
5259 edge.UpdateTo(control);
5260 }
5261 } else if (NodeProperties::IsEffectEdge(edge)) {
5262 edge.UpdateTo(effect);
5263 }
5264 }
5265
5266 selector->DeferReplacement(node, value);
5267}
5268
5269Node* SimplifiedLowering::Float64Round(Node* const node) {
5270 Node* const one = jsgraph()->Float64Constant(1.0);
5271 Node* const one_half = jsgraph()->Float64Constant(0.5);
5272 Node* const input = node->InputAt(0);
5273
5274 // Round up towards Infinity, and adjust if the difference exceeds 0.5.
5275 Node* result = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Float64RoundUp().placeholder(),
5276 node->InputAt(0));
5277 return graph()->NewNode(
5278 common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64),
5279 graph()->NewNode(
5280 machine()->Float64LessThanOrEqual(),
5281 graph()->NewNode(machine()->Float64Sub(), result, one_half), input),
5282 result, graph()->NewNode(machine()->Float64Sub(), result, one));
5283}
5284
5285Node* SimplifiedLowering::Float64Sign(Node* const node) {
5286 Node* const minus_one = jsgraph()->Float64Constant(-1.0);
5287 Node* const zero = jsgraph()->Float64Constant(0.0);
5288 Node* const one = jsgraph()->Float64Constant(1.0);
5289
5290 Node* const input = node->InputAt(0);
5291
5292 return graph()->NewNode(
5293 common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64),
5294 graph()->NewNode(machine()->Float64LessThan(), input, zero), minus_one,
5295 graph()->NewNode(
5296 common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kFloat64),
5297 graph()->NewNode(machine()->Float64LessThan(), zero, input), one,
5298 input));
5299}
5300
5301Node* SimplifiedLowering::Int32Abs(Node* const node) {
5302 Node* const input = node->InputAt(0);
5303
5304 // Generate case for absolute integer value.
5305 //
5306 // let sign = input >> 31 in
5307 // (input ^ sign) - sign
5308
5309 Node* sign = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32Sar(), input,
5310 jsgraph()->Int32Constant(31));
5311 return graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Sub(),
5312 graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32Xor(), input, sign),
5313 sign);
5314}
5315
5316Node* SimplifiedLowering::Int32Div(Node* const node) {
5317 Int32BinopMatcher m(node);
5318 Node* const zero = jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0);
5319 Node* const minus_one = jsgraph()->Int32Constant(-1);
5320 Node* const lhs = m.left().node();
5321 Node* const rhs = m.right().node();
5322
5323 if (m.right().Is(-1)) {
5324 return graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Sub(), zero, lhs);
5325 } else if (m.right().Is(0)) {
5326 return rhs;
5327 } else if (machine()->Int32DivIsSafe() || m.right().HasResolvedValue()) {
5328 return graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Div(), lhs, rhs, graph()->start());
5329 }
5330
5331 // General case for signed integer division.
5332 //
5333 // if 0 < rhs then
5334 // lhs / rhs
5335 // else
5336 // if rhs < -1 then
5337 // lhs / rhs
5338 // else if rhs == 0 then
5339 // 0
5340 // else
5341 // 0 - lhs
5342 //
5343 // Note: We do not use the Diamond helper class here, because it really hurts
5344 // readability with nested diamonds.
5345 const Operator* const merge_op = common()->Merge(2);
5346 const Operator* const phi_op =
5347 common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, 2);
5348
5349 Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32LessThan(), zero, rhs);
5350 Node* branch0 = graph()->NewNode(
5351 common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check0,
5352 graph()->start());
5353
5354 Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
5355 Node* true0 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Div(), lhs, rhs, if_true0);
5356
5357 Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
5358 Node* false0;
5359 {
5360 Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32LessThan(), rhs, minus_one);
5361 Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(
5362 common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check1,
5363 if_false0);
5364
5365 Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1);
5366 Node* true1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Div(), lhs, rhs, if_true1);
5367
5368 Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
5369 Node* false1;
5370 {
5371 Node* check2 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32Equal(), rhs, zero);
5372 Node* branch2 = graph()->NewNode(
5373 common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone, BranchSemantics::kMachine),
5374 check2, if_false1);
5375
5376 Node* if_true2 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch2);
5377 Node* true2 = zero;
5378
5379 Node* if_false2 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch2);
5380 Node* false2 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Sub(), zero, lhs);
5381
5382 if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true2, if_false2);
5383 false1 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true2, false2, if_false1);
5384 }
5385
5386 if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true1, if_false1);
5387 false0 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true1, false1, if_false0);
5388 }
5389
5390 Node* merge0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true0, if_false0);
5391 return graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true0, false0, merge0);
5392}
5393
5394Node* SimplifiedLowering::Int32Mod(Node* const node) {
5395 Int32BinopMatcher m(node);
5396 Node* const zero = jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0);
5397 Node* const minus_one = jsgraph()->Int32Constant(-1);
5398 Node* const lhs = m.left().node();
5399 Node* const rhs = m.right().node();
5400
5401 if (m.right().Is(-1) || m.right().Is(0)) {
5402 return zero;
5403 } else if (m.right().HasResolvedValue()) {
5404 return graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Mod(), lhs, rhs, graph()->start());
5405 }
5406
5407 // General case for signed integer modulus, with optimization for (unknown)
5408 // power of 2 right hand side.
5409 //
5410 // if 0 < rhs then
5411 // msk = rhs - 1
5412 // if rhs & msk != 0 then
5413 // lhs % rhs
5414 // else
5415 // if lhs < 0 then
5416 // -(-lhs & msk)
5417 // else
5418 // lhs & msk
5419 // else
5420 // if rhs < -1 then
5421 // lhs % rhs
5422 // else
5423 // zero
5424 //
5425 // Note: We do not use the Diamond helper class here, because it really hurts
5426 // readability with nested diamonds.
5427 const Operator* const merge_op = common()->Merge(2);
5428 const Operator* const phi_op =
5429 common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, 2);
5430
5431 Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32LessThan(), zero, rhs);
5432 Node* branch0 = graph()->NewNode(
5433 common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check0,
5434 graph()->start());
5435
5436 Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
5437 Node* true0;
5438 {
5439 Node* msk = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Add(), rhs, minus_one);
5440
5441 Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32And(), rhs, msk);
5442 Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(
5443 common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check1,
5444 if_true0);
5445
5446 Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1);
5447 Node* true1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Mod(), lhs, rhs, if_true1);
5448
5449 Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
5450 Node* false1;
5451 {
5452 Node* check2 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32LessThan(), lhs, zero);
5453 Node* branch2 = graph()->NewNode(
5454 common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse, BranchSemantics::kMachine),
5455 check2, if_false1);
5456
5457 Node* if_true2 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch2);
5458 Node* true2 = graph()->NewNode(
5459 machine()->Int32Sub(), zero,
5460 graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32And(),
5461 graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Sub(), zero, lhs),
5462 msk));
5463
5464 Node* if_false2 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch2);
5465 Node* false2 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32And(), lhs, msk);
5466
5467 if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true2, if_false2);
5468 false1 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true2, false2, if_false1);
5469 }
5470
5471 if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true1, if_false1);
5472 true0 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true1, false1, if_true0);
5473 }
5474
5475 Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
5476 Node* false0;
5477 {
5478 Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32LessThan(), rhs, minus_one);
5479 Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(
5480 common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check1,
5481 if_false0);
5482
5483 Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1);
5484 Node* true1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Mod(), lhs, rhs, if_true1);
5485
5486 Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
5487 Node* false1 = zero;
5488
5489 if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true1, if_false1);
5490 false0 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true1, false1, if_false0);
5491 }
5492
5493 Node* merge0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true0, if_false0);
5494 return graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true0, false0, merge0);
5495}
5496
5497Node* SimplifiedLowering::Int32Sign(Node* const node) {
5498 Node* const minus_one = jsgraph()->Int32Constant(-1);
5499 Node* const zero = jsgraph()->Int32Constant(0);
5500 Node* const one = jsgraph()->Int32Constant(1);
5501
5502 Node* const input = node->InputAt(0);
5503
5504 return graph()->NewNode(
5505 common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kWord32),
5506 graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32LessThan(), input, zero), minus_one,
5507 graph()->NewNode(
5508 common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kWord32),
5509 graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32LessThan(), zero, input), one,
5510 zero));
5511}
5512
5513Node* SimplifiedLowering::Uint32Div(Node* const node) {
5514 Uint32BinopMatcher m(node);
5515 Node* const zero = jsgraph()->Uint32Constant(0);
5516 Node* const lhs = m.left().node();
5517 Node* const rhs = m.right().node();
5518
5519 if (m.right().Is(0)) {
5520 return zero;
5521 } else if (machine()->Uint32DivIsSafe() || m.right().HasResolvedValue()) {
5522 return graph()->NewNode(machine()->Uint32Div(), lhs, rhs, graph()->start());
5523 }
5524
5525 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32Equal(), rhs, zero);
5526 Diamond d(graph(), common(), check, BranchHint::kFalse,
5527 BranchSemantics::kMachine);
5528 Node* div = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Uint32Div(), lhs, rhs, d.if_false);
5529 return d.Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, zero, div);
5530}
5531
5532Node* SimplifiedLowering::Uint32Mod(Node* const node) {
5533 Uint32BinopMatcher m(node);
5534 Node* const minus_one = jsgraph()->Int32Constant(-1);
5535 Node* const zero = jsgraph()->Uint32Constant(0);
5536 Node* const lhs = m.left().node();
5537 Node* const rhs = m.right().node();
5538
5539 if (m.right().Is(0)) {
5540 return zero;
5541 } else if (m.right().HasResolvedValue()) {
5542 return graph()->NewNode(machine()->Uint32Mod(), lhs, rhs, graph()->start());
5543 }
5544
5545 // General case for unsigned integer modulus, with optimization for (unknown)
5546 // power of 2 right hand side.
5547 //
5548 // if rhs == 0 then
5549 // zero
5550 // else
5551 // msk = rhs - 1
5552 // if rhs & msk != 0 then
5553 // lhs % rhs
5554 // else
5555 // lhs & msk
5556 //
5557 // Note: We do not use the Diamond helper class here, because it really hurts
5558 // readability with nested diamonds.
5559 const Operator* const merge_op = common()->Merge(2);
5560 const Operator* const phi_op =
5561 common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kWord32, 2);
5562
5563 Node* check0 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32Equal(), rhs, zero);
5564 Node* branch0 = graph()->NewNode(
5565 common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check0,
5566 graph()->start());
5567
5568 Node* if_true0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch0);
5569 Node* true0 = zero;
5570
5571 Node* if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch0);
5572 Node* false0;
5573 {
5574 Node* msk = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Int32Add(), rhs, minus_one);
5575
5576 Node* check1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32And(), rhs, msk);
5577 Node* branch1 = graph()->NewNode(
5578 common()->Branch(BranchHint::kNone, BranchSemantics::kMachine), check1,
5579 if_false0);
5580
5581 Node* if_true1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch1);
5582 Node* true1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Uint32Mod(), lhs, rhs, if_true1);
5583
5584 Node* if_false1 = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch1);
5585 Node* false1 = graph()->NewNode(machine()->Word32And(), lhs, msk);
5586
5587 if_false0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true1, if_false1);
5588 false0 = graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true1, false1, if_false0);
5589 }
5590
5591 Node* merge0 = graph()->NewNode(merge_op, if_true0, if_false0);
5592 return graph()->NewNode(phi_op, true0, false0, merge0);
5593}
5594
5595void SimplifiedLowering::DoMax(Node* node, Operator const* op,
5596 MachineRepresentation rep) {
5597 Node* const lhs = node->InputAt(0);
5598 Node* const rhs = node->InputAt(1);
5599
5600 node->ReplaceInput(0, graph()->NewNode(op, lhs, rhs));
5601 DCHECK_EQ(rhs, node->InputAt(1));
5602 node->AppendInput(graph()->zone(), lhs);
5603 ChangeOp(node, common()->Select(rep));
5604}
5605
5606void SimplifiedLowering::DoMin(Node* node, Operator const* op,
5607 MachineRepresentation rep) {
5608 Node* const lhs = node->InputAt(0);
5609 Node* const rhs = node->InputAt(1);
5610
5611 node->InsertInput(graph()->zone(), 0, graph()->NewNode(op, lhs, rhs));
5612 DCHECK_EQ(lhs, node->InputAt(1));
5613 DCHECK_EQ(rhs, node->InputAt(2));
5614 ChangeOp(node, common()->Select(rep));
5615}

5621

5623 node->AppendInput(graph()->zone(), zero);
5624 ChangeOp(node, op);
5625}
